According to British media, Admiral William Moran, deputy secretary of naval operations, said that even as the U.S. Navy is revitalizing its efforts to deal with an increasingly worrying Russia on both sides of the Atlantic, the United States continues to focus on the Asia-Pacific region, which the Pentagon has expanded to include the Indian Ocean-Asia-Pacific Ocean.
The United States has listed China and Russia as strategic competitors in its new defense strategy released at the beginning of the year, the website of Jane's Defense Weekly reported on September 24.
The U.S. Navy has since restored the Second Fleet in order to more directly counter Russian activities.
The moves raised some questions and concerns among allies and analysts that the U.S. Navy could move away from the "Asia-Pacific rebalancing" strategy that marked the Obama administration, the report said.
But Admiral Moran said the U.S. Navy's focus remains on the western Pacific.
"For us, there has been no significant change," he said at a round-table discussion called "Addressing the High Seas Challenge," hosted by the U.S. National Bureau of Asian Studies in Washington on January 24, 2018.
"The focus is still on rebalancing, shifting the center of gravity or whatever you want to describe it." Moran said.
But he acknowledged that the United States has close ties to Europe.
"We will continue to focus on growth on the West Coast and balance what we can do." he said.
While Moran noted that overall policy on Russia falls within the purview of the U.S. defense secretary, he warned: "The Russians may face demographic and economic challenges, but history has proved that they can be very tough if we clash with them."
Admiral Moran said that as part of a U.S. comeback against Russia, China and other competitors, the U.S. Navy is dynamically deploying troops into a "new mode of operations," which will help keep adversaries off guard about where U.S. carrier battle groups or other assets will be deployed at any given time and place.
"Our Navy and Marine Corps support it-the concept of operational unpredictability, not being in the same place over and over again, almost like clockwork-that's our approach." he said.
The first to try the new approach was the Harry Truman carrier battle group, whose early deployment included working visits to the port and patrols in areas that usually only pass, the report said.
Moran said the U.S. Navy is now working to ensure allies know that the warships will still patrol traditional areas, and is also addressing logistical and family liaison issues for the new deployment process.
The commander of the Royal Australian Navy, Lieutenant General Michael Nunan, also spoke at the event, saying Australian troops could work seamlessly with the U.S. aircraft carrier battle group.
He said the situation would continue as the Royal Australian Navy plans to procure nine more frigates equipped with the "Zeus Shield" combat system.
A number of airlines will raise or resume fuel surcharges from October 5. Air travel will have to be increased from Friday
Yesterday, airlines such as Xiangpeng Airlines and Okai Airlines announced that from October 5, 2018 (the date of issue), each passenger on domestic routes under 800 km (including) will be charged a fuel surcharge of 20 yuan and each passenger on routes over 800 km will be charged a fuel surcharge of 30 yuan.
Companies such as Xiangpeng Airlines and Okai Airlines announced that from 0:00 on October 5, 2018 (the date of issue), the fuel surcharge on domestic routes under 800 km (including) will be raised from 10 yuan per person to 20 yuan per person, and the fuel surcharge on domestic routes over 800 km will be raised from 10 yuan per person to 30 yuan per person.
Children, military and police disabilities are 10 yuan per person; babies continue to be exempted.
According to the relevant person-in-charge of Ctrip Ticket, the airline has indicated in the notice that the fuel surcharge is charged on the original date of issue, and that the fuel surcharge will not be refunded when the ticket is replaced.
This means that domestic route tickets issued before 5 October will not have to pay the fuel surcharge in accordance with the new standard if they are to be changed to after 5 October (including).
Since June 5, 2018, a number of airlines, including Air China, Eastern Airlines, Air China, Shanghai Airlines, Spring and Autumn Airlines, Shenzhen Airlines, Western Airlines and Okai Airlines, have resumed collecting fuel surcharges on domestic routes that have been cancelled for three years, with a standard of 10 yuan per person.
This time, Xiangpeng Airlines, Okai Airlines took the lead in announcing an increase in the fuel surcharge, as of the press release, has not seen the four major domestic airlines announce the follow-up adjustment.
It is also understood that the Civil Aviation Department of Hong Kong has stipulated that airlines can decide for themselves whether to charge a fuel surcharge from November.
Cathay Pacific first announced on September 27 that it would collect a fuel surcharge on November 2.
According to the Cathay Pacific website, all tickets issued or re-issued by Cathay Pacific and Cathay Pacific Dragon Airlines on or after 2 November will include a fuel surcharge, a fuel surcharge of 652 yuan for long-distance flights to and from Hong Kong and the South-West Pacific, North America, Europe, the Middle East and India, and Africa, and a fuel surcharge of 146 yuan for short-haul flights.
The fee applies to all types of tickets, calculated on the basis of each segment, and includes ticket quotations on all direct selling channels in Cathay Pacific.
On the eve of the 69th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China, Chinese Premier Li Keqiang met with new ambassadors from 29 countries and regions to China at the Great Hall of the People on the afternoon of the 30th.
Li Keqiang shook hands with the envoys in China and had a cordial conversation.
Li Keqiang welcomed the envoys to China to take up their new duties and asked them to convey their sincere greetings and good wishes to the leaders and people of the countries concerned and the leaders of relevant institutions.
Li Keqiang made positive comments on China's good relations with other countries and regions, stressed China's commitment to enhancing bilateral political mutual trust, deepening practical cooperation and strengthening coordination and cooperation in international and regional affairs, and hoped that the envoys would walk more, see more and make new positive contributions to the development of China's relations with their respective countries and regions in their new posts.
The Chinese Government is ready to facilitate and support the envoys in the performance of their duties.
Li Keqiang pointed out that China adheres to the path of peaceful development and unswervingly promotes economic globalization.
This year marks the 40th anniversary of China's reform and opening-up. As the largest developing country in the world, we are ready to achieve common development with other countries in further expanding its opening-up.
In the context of the rise of protectionism and unilateralism, we are ready to work with all parties to continue to consolidate and strengthen partnerships on the basis of the principles of mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit, promote the strategy of docking development, promote cooperation in the construction of the "one-way road" on the basis of the principle of joint construction and sharing, work together to safeguard multilateralism and free trade, jointly build an open world economy, and give new impetus to the stable and balanced development of the world economy.
Envoys from various countries and institutions in China warmly congratulated the People's Republic of China on its 69th anniversary, conveyed the greetings of the leaders of their respective countries and institutions to the Chinese leaders and people, and said that China has made outstanding achievements in development and believes that further deepening reform and expanding opening-up in the future will bring more opportunities for development to the world.
We are ready to play an active role in promoting friendly cooperation between their respective countries and regions and China and better achieving mutual benefit and win-win progress.
Subsequently, envoys from various countries and institutions in China attended the National Day reception at the invitation of Li Keqiang.
State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi attended the event.
TOKYO (Reuters) -Japan's Itozhong Commercial on Friday recognized a US $1.3 billion impairment loss on its investment in China's CITIC shares, writing down its largest corporate investment deal because of trade tensions between China and the United States.
A man walks past the headquarters of the company in Tokyo, Japan, in May 2016.
Meatball, for its part, said the trade war had hit Gao Hong, its U.S. grain division, and that it had suspended financial transactions in agriculture.
Some Japanese heavy equipment manufacturers, telecoms companies and others have warned of the impact of trade frictions between China and the United States when they report their latest results, and now they have joined the ranks.
The United States and China impose tariffs on each other's hundreds of billions of dollars of goods, and U.S. President Trump has threatened to extend the tax to all more than US $500 billion of Chinese goods exported to the United States if the dispute is not resolved.
Tsuyoshi Hachimura, Itozhong's commercial finance chief, said the trade dispute could have a greater impact on China's economy next year.
Itozhong Commercial and Thailand's Bu Bee Group invested US $10 billion in CITIC in 2015 to take a 20% stake in it.
Hachimura said Itozhong reported a loss of 143.3 billion yen (US $1.3 billion) on the stake because it did not think CITIC's share price would recover in the near future.
Itozhong maintained its profit forecast for the fiscal year ending March 31, 2019 at 500 billion yen.
In July, China imposed a 25% import tariff on U.S. soybeans to counter Washington's move in trade frictions.
"Our grain business has been hit by trade frictions between the United States and China," said Yanhong, the finance chief.
He said Gaohong had stopped financial transactions in his own account since September.
Gaohong spokesman Pat Burke said in a draft statement on Friday that the company's move was "in accordance with internal policy restrictions and due to a lack of market opportunities."
He also said the suspension of financial transactions would not lead to fewer jobs.
Meatball maintained its annual profit forecast of 230 billion yen, helped by pulp and paper and power generation.
Sumitomo Commercial on Thursday reported a 16% increase in profit between April and September, stressing that "U.S. trade problems with China have led to an uncertain outlook."
Mitsubishi raised its annual profit forecast to a record level on Friday due to higher coking coal production and higher commodity prices such as oil and coal.
Mitsubishi also announced a new business plan to boost its profit to 900 billion yen (US $7.98 billion) in the fiscal year ending March 31, 2022 from an estimated 640 billion yen this year.
Voting in the U.S. midterm elections has entered the countdown, according to a comprehensive report on November 5.
On November 4, President Trump and his Democratic opponents actively "urged votes" to their core voters.
Both major parties point out that voter turnout will be the key to shaping the election.
Forty-eight hours before the U.S. popular vote, Trump was reportedly busy attending the Republican candidate's momentum-building event, while former President Barack Obama went to Indiana to platform Joe Donnelly, the Democratic federal Senate candidate who was in a hurry, and called out his final pre-election appeal to the crowd.
On November 4, Trump went to the platform for Republican gubernatorial candidate Brian Kemp in Megang, Georgia, and said, "You have to go to the polling place on Tuesday, you have to vote."
"The contrast in this election could not have been clearer."
Voters' political enthusiasm has risen to a rare peak, with early voting far more than usual in some states.
Successive U.S. presidents face their first midterm elections, and his party tends to have fewer members of Congress.
While the Democratic federal House race remains dominant, Republicans could benefit from economic assessments and Trump's strict focus on border security, according to a new poll released by the Washington Post and ABC News on Thursday.
Polls show that registered voters like more Democratic House candidates than Republicans, 50% to 43%, but are still down from a 14-point lead in August.
A separate poll by NBC and the Wall Street Journal also showed Democrats still seven points ahead of Republicans.
"When people don't tell the truth, when words no longer represent anything, it's bound to have bad results," Obama is understood to have told the crowd at Senator Donoli's rally.
Democracy can't work when people can only lie to themselves. "
"The only way to stop the behavior of these Republicans now is you and your vote." "
Democrats face their most difficult election in decades in the Senate, where Republicans now hold more than half of the 51 seats.
But the House race is more favorable, and Democrats need to win 23 more seats to take control of the 435-seat House.
Analysts at FiveThirtyEight.com, a predictive election website, estimate that Democrats have an 85% chance of winning the House.
