North Korean Foreign Minister Lee Yong-ho told the United Nations on Saturday that continued sanctions were deepening North Korea's distrust of the United States and that North Korea could not unilaterally give up its nuclear weapons in such a situation.
Speaking at the United Nations General Assembly, Lee Yong-ho said North Korea had taken a "very friendly approach" over the past year, including halting missile and nuclear tests, dismantling nuclear test sites and committing to non-proliferation of nuclear weapons and nuclear technology.
"But we have not seen any corresponding response from the United States," he said.
"If we do not trust the United States, we have no confidence in our national security, and in such a situation, we cannot unilaterally give up our weapons first." he said.
While Lee Yong-ho was repeating North Korea's complaints about the United States' opposition to "phased" denuclearization, his speech was significant because there was no complete rejection of unilateral denuclearization, as North Korea had done before.
Lee Yong-ho referred to a joint statement by Kim Jong-un and Trump on June 12, when Kim Jong-un agreed to efforts to "denuclearize the Korean peninsula" and Trump promised to protect North Korea's security.
North Korea has been seeking a formal end to the 1950-53 Korean War, but the United States says it must give up its nuclear weapons first.
The United States has also refused to ease demands for international sanctions against North Korea.
"The United States insists on'denuclearization first 'and has increased pressure on sanctions to achieve its goals in a high-pressure manner, and has even refused to issue a'declaration on the end of the war'," Li said.
"The idea that sanctions can make us kneel for mercy is that people who don't know us are daydreaming.
But the problem is that such continued sanctions are deepening our mistrust. "
Li Yong-ho did not mention the plans for a second special gold conference mentioned by the U.S. president at the United Nations earlier this week.
Instead, he highlighted three meetings between Kim Jong Un and South Korean President Moon Jae-in over the past five months and said: "If the other side of denuclearization is South Korea, not North Korea, the denuclearization of the Korean peninsula will not become so deadlocked."
China has announced a reduction in import tariffs on 1,585 tariff lines from November 1, 2018.
Since the beginning of this year, China has taken the initiative to reduce import tariffs.
On May 1 this year, the tax on drugs was reduced in an all-round way, adjusting the import tariffs on 28 tax items, including all ordinary drugs, including anti-cancer drugs, alkaloid drugs with anti-cancer effects and Chinese-made drugs actually imported, to zero.
At the same time, the value-added tax burden on the production and import of anti-cancer drugs has been greatly reduced.
On July 1, taxes were reduced on cars and spare parts for 218 tax items.
After tax, China's total car tax rate has been lower than the average of developing countries and is in line with the actual situation of China's auto industry.
The tax reduction will promote the restructuring of the industry and the optimal allocation of resources, accelerate the survival of winners and losers, help to improve the quality of products and services, and is expected to promote the adjustment of car prices to a certain extent and give consumers more benefits.
On July 1, taxes were reduced on daily consumer goods for 1,449 tax items.
The tax reduction on consumer goods is closely related to the needs of the people for a better life.
The tax reduction is not only large in number but also strong, with an average tax reduction of 56%.
Tax cuts on daily consumer goods directly benefit consumers and promote the competitiveness of domestic industries.
On November 1, tax cuts will be imposed on industrial goods such as electromechanical equipment, spare parts and raw materials for 1,585 tax items.
An appropriate reduction in import tariffs on some of the industrial goods that are urgently needed in China will attract more foreign investment, help to increase effective domestic supply and help to upgrade industries. At the same time, it will help enterprises to allocate resources worldwide, reduce production costs and reduce the pressure on the domestic environment.
The above four independent tax cuts, as well as the third step of the tax cuts implemented on July 1 this year in accordance with the outcome of the negotiations on the expansion of the scope of the information technology agreement, will reduce China's overall tariff level to 7.5% from 9.8% the previous year, according to a person in charge of the office of the Committee on Tariffs and Tariffs of the State Council.
The overall level of adjusted tariffs is slightly higher than that of the European Union, lower than that of most developing countries, and is at a medium-low level, which is basically in line with China's status as a developing country and stage of development.
The person in charge introduced that the total tariff level, as one of the important indicators of China's openness in the field of trade in goods, should be in line with the stage of China's economic development and reflect the characteristics of the times.
China's trade in goods is the largest in the world and already has an economic base for further expansion and opening-up, but there is still a gap between the quality and efficiency of trade development and that of developed economies. Therefore, the overall tariff level should be appropriately reduced.
Tariffs are a means of compliance protection. The level of tariffs should be in line with the competitiveness of the industry. Benign competition should be encouraged. Excessive protection is not conducive to industrial development and quality improvement.
The adjustment of tariff rate should take into account the needs of production and consumption demand.
Emphasis has been placed on reducing the commodity tax rate, which has large domestic demand and is conducive to industrial transformation and upgrading, and efforts have been made to increase the import of products with special advantages where the needs of the people are concentrated, continuously enhancing the sense of access of enterprises and the public, and meeting the needs of upgrading the industrial structure and consumption structure.
The intensity of tax reduction should take into account the affordability of fiscal revenue and industrial development.
In the choice of specific tax reduction commodities and tax reduction ranges, we should coordinate the two domestic and foreign markets, the upper and lower reaches, and the relationship between production and consumption, so as to maintain the steady and positive momentum of China's economic development.
The person in charge stressed that this year marks the 40th anniversary of reform and opening-up, and that China's initiative to reduce the overall level of import tariffs is a major step taken in accordance with China's own needs to achieve high-quality development, which is conducive to the overall use of both international and foreign resources, the improvement of the quality of the domestic supply system and the meeting of the needs of the people for the upgrading of consumption.
This action and initiative show that China will unswervingly pursue a mutually beneficial and win-win opening-up strategy, firmly support economic globalization, resolutely safeguard the principle of free trade and the multilateral trading system with the WTO at its core, continue to draw the impetus for development from opening up to the world and make China's development better benefit the world.
Serbia announces highest state of readiness The President of Serbia and Russia will meet tomorrow to discuss the situation in Kosovo
Serbian President Vucic has ordered the country's armed forces to enter a state of maximum operational readiness in view of the occupation by Kosovo special forces of the access to the water storage lake of the Ghazivoda Hydropower Station in northern Kosovo, which is controlled by the Belgrade side, Nantong said, citing the Office of the President of Serbia.
On 29 September, the Serbian Minister of Defence, Vulin, declared that the Serbian army had entered a state of full operational readiness.
Wulin stressed that as long as the order issued by Vucic remains in force, Serbia will continue to monitor the current situation in Kosovo and that the SLA will respond regardless of the direction of the situation.
On September 29, Vucic said in an interview that he had briefed parties such as the United States, Russia and Europe on the current situation and would travel to Moscow on October 2 to meet with Russian President Vladimir Putin to seek Putin's support on Kosovo, according to Russian news agency Tass.
Asked if Serbia needed Russian military support like Syria, Vucic gave a negative response: "I don't want a major military conflict on our territory."
Vucic also said the SLA had entered a full state of readiness only to form a deterrent to stop the conflict, but it was also a clear warning that no violence in Kosovo would be tolerated.
The reason why the SLA has increased its operational readiness is related to two major moves by the Kosovo side.
According to the Serbian side, in recent days, Albanians have been arresting Serbs who have lived there for generations in northern Kosovo, and the arrested Serbs have not broken any law.
According to Vucic, since the beating and detention of Marko Yulic, head of the Kosovo and Metohija Office of the Government of Serbia, by the Kosovo Afghan Army on 26 March this year, ethnic Albanians have been escalating the situation in the region, carrying out inhuman arrests and evictions of Serbs.
In addition, more than 100 people, including the ROSU special forces of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Republic of Kosovo, armed police and snipers, who had recently announced their establishment, occupied positions near the water storage lake of the Ghazivoda Hydropower Station, entered the ecological and sports centre near the dam in the northern part of the Kosovo region and blocked all nearby roads, which were originally under the control of the Serbian side.
Vucic noted that the military adventure in Kosovo was carried out at the instigation of Western countries and that the move by the Kosovo army did not inform the Serbian side in advance, in violation of chapter IX, paragraph 1, of the Brussels Agreement, as well as United Nations Security Council resolution 1244 and the military technical agreement between Serbia and Kosovo.
Vucic has shouted to NATO Secretary-General Jens Stoltenberg, criticizing Western countries' hypocritical rhetoric on Kosovo.
The root cause of the current conflict is still a centuries-old historical feud between the two communities in Kosovo.
With regard to the attribution of Kosovo, the Serbs and Albanians have their own accounts.
Serbia sees Kosovo as the birthplace of the nation and the cradle of culture, where Serbia established its strongest state in the 12th century, and ethnic Albanians moved in large numbers only after the invasion of the Ottoman Empire and the defeat of the SLA to the north.
Albanians, for their part, insist that the Ilirians, the original tribe that lived in Kosovo in the 4th-5th century BC, were the ancestors of ethnic Albanians and that Kosovo has therefore been ethnic Albanian territory since ancient times.
Subjective political divisions have led to violent clashes between different ethnic groups, religions and cultures, resulting in a fierce confrontation between Serbs and Albanians in Kosovo.
In 1912, Kosovo Albanians first declared Albania's independence.
After the First World War, a large number of Albanians living in the Balkans moved to Turkey, and the proportion of Serbs increased relatively. In the view of the Serbs, the practice of "just taking back their own land" was seen by the Albanians as a plunder of "Greater Serbia", and the conflict between the two communities intensified.
Kosovo has become a "powder keg" in the Balkans.
In 1999, armed clashes between Albanian separatists in the Kosovo Liberation Army and the Serbian army and police led to the bombing of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia made up of Serbia and Montenegro by NATO forces and the outbreak of the war in Kosovo.
On 17 February 2008, Kosovo unilaterally declared independence from Serbia.
Since then, it has been reported that Serbia will normalize relations with Kosovo and sign a global and legally binding agreement, but the agreement, which is subject to multiple forces, including the United States, Europe and Russia, has not been signed because of historical national vendetta and geopolitical constraints.
Just a month ago, Vucic made it clear for the first time that he advocated the separation of Serbs and Albanians in Kosovo and once again the openness of the conflict between the two communities.
Power communications still disrupted in Indonesia's strong earthquake with tsunami rescue difficulties
According to figures released by Indonesia's Disaster Relief Agency in the early hours of the morning, 420 people have been killed in a powerful earthquake and tsunami in Donggara County, Central Sulawesi Province, on the 28th.
Willem Rampangilei, head of Indonesia's disaster relief agency, said the figure was only preliminary statistics from the city of Palu, Central Sulawesi province, about 80 kilometers from the epicenter, and that many of the city's densely populated buildings, such as hotels, shopping malls and warehouses, which were damaged by the earthquake, had not yet been searched because of a lack of large search and rescue machinery.
A bridge damaged by an earthquake and tsunami collapses into sections on Ba Road, Indonesia, on September 29, 2018 local time.
As a result of the serious damage to power and communications facilities, the epicenter of the earthquake, Dongara County, and the adjacent Xigi area, are still unconnected "isolated islands" and the number of victims cannot be counted.
Indonesian Vice President Kara said the death toll could reach thousands, the media reported.
Power outages, communications outages, road blockages, airport damage... rescue efforts after the strong earthquake and tsunami are difficult.
As a result of the power outage, some hospitals and rescue settlements in the city of Palu have to rely on fuel to generate electricity.
Roads in and out of the city were blocked by landslides and large transport vehicles, including fuel tankers, were unable to enter, making fuel supplies tight.
Indonesia's social minister, Agus, said emergency relief supplies such as tents, mattresses, blankets, clothing, food and household goods packages transferred by the ministry from the provinces of South Sulawesi and Columbus, near the quake zone, had not yet arrived in the disaster area because of road damage.
Disaster relief materials transferred from the capital, Jakarta, are being transported to the disaster area via air force transport planes.
In view of the damage to the command tower and runway at Paru Airport in the earthquake, in order to ensure safety and security of rescue, all commercial flights have been suspended for the departure and landing of military aircraft carrying relief supplies and personnel only.
Indonesia's chief minister for political, legal and security affairs, Villanto, who directed the rescue in the quake zone, called for the restoration of power supplies and commercial flight services at the airport as soon as possible to ensure the operation of rescue agencies such as hospitals and allow more rescue workers, volunteers and aid to reach the disaster area.
A number of powerful earthquakes occurred in Donggara County, Central Sulawesi Province, Indonesia, on the 28th, including a powerful 7.7-magnitude earthquake at 1702 hours local time that triggered a tsunami, causing major disasters in the cities of Palu, Dongara County and Xigi.
BEIJING, Oct 1 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has continued to open the most beautiful blue sky model, attracting thousands of people in the capital to show their happiness on social platforms and continue to brush their screens, saying that "under the blue sky and white clouds, 'drunk 'the beautiful skyline, this is the best business card in Beijing".
Since August, Beijing has ushered in the "bluest sky".
Within the capital, people can be seen at any time and anywhere, either holding smartphones or holding a single-reverse camera to take photos.
Weibo, microblogging friends circle and other social platforms, can be seen everywhere in the netizen's lens of the Palace Museum, Tiananmen Square, Bird's Nest, Hutong... all kinds of buildings show different beauty against the blue sky.
Some netizens said that such a "big picture of scenery" is the best urban propaganda film in Beijing; others quipped that if such a blue sky is brushed for a long time, people with cervical spondylopathy can be cured; and some netizens hoped that "this blue can cross the winter and welcome the spring and summer, so that the sky in the capital is blue in the four seasons".
Why do the people of the capital particularly love to bask in the blue sky?
Only because people living in the city in the past have suffered from haze and haze, they are particularly eager for the blue sky, and after the "blue sky defense war" in Beijing, which has continued to improve air quality, the haze has become less and the blue sky has increased.
On National Day, the weather in Beijing is fine.
At 8 a.m., the vast majority of the city's 35 air quality monitoring stations showed "first-class excellent" green.
The "Bluest Sky" theme photography competition, which is spontaneous by the public on the social platform, is continuing.
Why is the sky so blue in Beijing recently?
In August, the average concentration of fine particulate matter (PM2.5) in Beijing was 35 ug / cubic meter, the best record for the same period in nearly five years, according to the head of the Beijing Environmental Protection Bureau.
The real-time concentration of PM2.5 in September was more frequent in single digits.
One of the main factors in the emergence of the "bluest sky" is that meteorological conditions have been generally favourable in recent years. More importantly, Beijing's consistent efforts to combat air pollution, its efforts to promote a clean air action plan over the past five years, and the continued release of environmental benefits have led to a reduction in the total amount of pollutant emissions in the region, all of which have laid the foundation for the sustained improvement of air quality.
Beijing officially released and implemented the Beijing Clean Air Action Plan 2013-2017 in 2013.
Under the plan, officials continue to guide the dredging of non-capital functions, promote clean energy replacement and pollution reduction, and phase out 4,923 coal-fired boilers.
As a result, Beijing has also become the first big city in mainland China to achieve full-net natural gas.
According to the data, between 2013 and 2017, the average annual concentration of PM2.5 in Beijing fell by 35.6%; the number of days of air quality standards increased by 50 days; the number of days of first-class excellence increased by 25 days; the number of days of heavy pollution decreased by 35 days, and the incidence of heavy pollution decreased significantly.
While air quality has continued to improve, Beijing officials, on the basis of a new round of PM2.5 source analysis, issued the "Three-Year Action Plan for Beijing to Win the Blue Sky Guard War" in September this year. In view of the current stage of control and pollution characteristics, they have focused on key areas of prevention and control such as diesel trucks, dust and volatile organic matter control, optimized and adjusted the transport structure, industrial structure, energy structure and land use structure, strengthened regional joint prevention and control, focused on strengthening the refined management of the city, promoting green development in an all-round way, and striving to make the "bluest sky" resident in the capital no longer the background of the people's photo album.
