With active treatment, the survival rate of premature babies of 29 weeks or more in China has reached 98%, which has reached the level of developed countries.
SHANGHAI, Sept 30 (Chen Jing Luo Yanqian) The National Children's Medical Center and the Pediatric Hospital Affiliated to Fudan University revealed on the 30th that it had introduced advanced Canadian methods in the leading "China NICU Inpatient Premature Infants' Prognosis Quality Improvement Project".
The results of the project show that, after active treatment, the survival rate of premature babies of 29 weeks and above in China has reached 98%, which has reached the level of developed countries, but there is still much room for improvement in the survival rate of premature babies of very small fetal age and premature babies without complications.
For nearly 20 years, the Chinese government has been paying attention to the treatment of newborns.
At present, the infant mortality rate in Shanghai has fallen to 3.71 per 1,000, which is significantly lower than the national average and has reached the advanced level of developed countries.
The "China NICU Inpatient Premature Infants Prognosis Quality Improvement Project" has greatly improved the quality of life of premature babies through four years of unremitting efforts.
Professor Cao Yun, director of the Neonatal Intensive Care Unit (NICU) of the Pediatrics Hospital attached to Fudan University, told reporters that while improving the survival rate of premature babies, paying attention to reducing the quality of survival of premature babies, reducing the incidence of complications, improving the prognosis of neurodevelopment and improving the overall outcome of children is of great significance to improving the overall quality of life and the quality of the population of premature babies. It is an important issue of concern to the paediatrics and Cenozoic paediatrics circles at home and abroad, as well as a key issue of concern to the project.
Through four years of unremitting efforts, the NICU Project for the Improvement of the Quality of Prognosis of Inpatient Premature Infants in China has included tens of thousands of premature babies aged 33 weeks or less across the country, resulting in a one-third reduction in the mortality rate of premature babies of small birth age and small birth weight in China, while the incidence of serious complications in premature babies has decreased significantly, greatly improving the quality of life of premature babies.
Through the establishment of a national network for the improvement of the quality of newborns, the introduction of the concept of cooperative quality improvement, the radiation of 25 cooperative hospitals throughout China, and the establishment of a complete, systematic and effective method for the improvement of the quality of cooperation in improving the prognosis of premature babies and improving the level of treatment of newborns, which is suitable for the national conditions.
The Pediatrics Hospital attached to Fudan University, in conjunction with the National Cenozoic Pediatrics Force, is accumulating experience on the basis of the project to formulate guidelines for the diagnosis and treatment of neonatal infections, so as to provide reference and guidance for the standardized diagnosis and treatment of neonatal infections in China.
It is understood that in the "Project to Improve the Quality of Prognosis of Premature Infants in China," paediatric hospitals have introduced the EPIQ method into 25 large NICUs in 19 provinces across the country, working to solve the problem of infection of premature babies that has plagued China's neonatal care rooms.
After more than 10 years of continuous improvement, Canada's complication-free survival rate for premature babies has increased by about one-third, and Canada is now one of the best countries in the world for the prognosis of premature babies.
The EPIQ method has now been applied to all NICUs across Canada and has been adopted by six countries.
The paediatric hospital revealed that the results showed that two years after EPIQ intervention, infections in premature babies fell by 35%, while antibiotic use fell by 20%.
In the future, the Pediatric Hospital attached to Fudan University will continue to popularize and implement this method throughout the country, with a view to reducing the incidence of all complications in premature babies in an all-round way and improving the quality of treatment for newborns throughout the country.
At present, it is an indisputable fact that there are differences and heterogeneity in the level of treatment in China.
According to Professor Cao Yun, as an important construction unit of the National Children's Medical Center, the paediatric hospital will play a leading role in radiation. The study covers a number of western provinces, including Xinjiang, Guizhou, Gansu and Shaanxi, with a view to gradually promoting the homogeneity and standardization of neonatal treatment throughout the country.
It is understood that the Pediatric Hospital attached to Fudan University, in conjunction with the National Cenozoic Pediatrics Force, is accumulating experience on the basis of the project to formulate guidelines for the diagnosis and treatment of neonatal infections, so as to provide reference and guidance for the standardized diagnosis and treatment of neonatal infections in China.
It was revealed that in 2019, the China Neonatal Co-operation Network, located at the Pediatrics Hospital attached to Fudan University, will work with 63 hospitals across the country to carry out the next phase of national quality improvement, with a view to promoting the uniform development of the level of neonatal treatment in China.
Wu Shenglei, director of the Shanghai Municipal Health and Family Planning Commission, said that Shanghai's ability to become a central city in the heart of Asia is not only reflected in research, but also in the construction of the whole service system, the quality of service and the results of service should have a place in Asia, thus truly reflecting China's medical level.
