The Turkish team, which entered the second set, served very hard and took a 6-2 lead at the start. The Chinese team adjusted its formation after asking for a timeout, gradually tied the score to 7, and then blocked the net several times to score 7-0. At the end of the set, the Turkish team chased the score to 15:19 at one point; after the Chinese team got the set point at 24:20, the tenacious Turkish team chased two points in a row; and after the Chinese team again asked for a timeout, they won the second set 25-23 with Zhu Ting's running attack.
In the third set, the situation was very glued, the score between the two sides rose alternately, at one point tied at 19.
At the crucial moment, the Turkish team made a mistake. After taking a 21: 19 lead, the Chinese team won the match point at 24:21 with Zhu Ting's strong smash and Zhang Changning's attack. The Turkish team then chased the score to 23:24. After the Chinese team asked for a timeout, Zhang Changning scored in attack and the Chinese team locked in a 25-23 victory.
Chinese women's volleyball coach Lang Ping admitted after the match that the whole game was not easy.
"We are well prepared, the blocking is good, the Turkish team is more comprehensive, we have to reduce our mistakes and try to win by scoring on our own initiative." he said.
In the face of her familiar team-mates in the past, Zhu Ting, who played for Turkey's Wakiver Bank team, was limited in the first set of the day's match, and then she took the initiative to change and still played a strong attack.
"They are familiar with each other and it is normal to be targeted by their opponents, but the Chinese team played to the extreme, blocking and attacking well in the face of a bad pass." he said.
The Chinese women's volleyball team will next have a day of truce for physical and technical training, and will face Canada, the third opponent in the group stage, on October 2.
