Nearly a thousand state-owned scenic spots cut ticket prices by more than half by more than 20%
As of September 28, 981 scenic spots had been opened or reduced free of charge (74 were opened free of charge and 907 were reduced), and scenic spots such as Shilin, Dali Santa, Yulong Xueshan, Guilin, Guangxi, Wuyi Mountain, Fujian Province, Zhangjiajie, Hunan Province, Terracotta Warriors and Horses in Shaanxi Province, Sanqing Mountain, Jiangxi Province, and Kanas, Xinjiang, had all been reduced.
In order to implement the decision-making and deployment of the Central Economic Work Conference and the Report on the Work of the Government, the National Development and Reform Commission issued the Guiding Opinions on Improving the Mechanism for the Formation of Ticket Prices in State-owned Scenic Areas to Reduce Ticket Prices in Key State-owned Scenic Areas (hereinafter referred to as the Guiding Opinions) on June 28, which call for the improvement of the mechanism for the formation of ticket prices in state-owned scenic spots in terms of rationally defining the composition of ticket pricing costs, innovating price management methods and strictly implementing pricing procedures, so as to ensure that the reduction of ticket prices in key state-owned scenic spots by the end of September has achieved remarkable results.
In accordance with the deployment requirements, all localities have actively carried out their work, and have successively reduced the price of tickets for a number of key state-owned scenic spots.
As of September 28, 981 scenic spots had been opened free of charge or reduced prices (74 were opened free of charge and 907 were reduced), of which 159 were 5A-level scenic spots and 534 were 4A-level scenic spots, totalling 693, or 70.6%.
Of the 907 scenic spots with reduced prices, 491, or 54.3%, fell by more than 20%, and 214, or 23.6%, fell by more than 30%.
Yunnan, Shandong, Guangxi, Shaanxi and other provinces have a large number of price-cutting scenic spots, of which the number of price-cutting scenic spots in Yunnan is more than 100, an overall decrease of more than 30%.
Anhui, Chongqing and other 8 provinces (districts, cities) government pricing 5A-level scenic spots all realized price reduction.
Scenic areas such as Shilin, Dali Santa, Yulong Snow Mountain, Lijiang River in Guilin, Guangxi, Wuyi Mountain in Fujian Province, Zhangjiajie in Hunan Province, Terracotta Warriors and Horses in Shaanxi Province, Sanqing Mountain in Jiangxi Province and Kanas in Xinjiang, which have high social attention, have all implemented price cuts.
The gradual return of ticket prices to a reasonable range in key state-owned scenic spots is conducive to accelerating the transformation and upgrading of tourism from the ticket economy to the industrial economy, small-scale tourism to mass tourism and scenic spot tourism to the whole region, forming a virtuous circle of optimization of the supply structure of tourism and steady expansion of the demand for tourism consumption, and promoting the sustained and healthy development of scenic spots and tourism.
At the same time, the National Development and Reform Commission stressed that all localities should strengthen the regulation of price order in scenic spots, guide scenic spots to upgrade their services and ensure that price cuts do not reduce quality.
In addition, the National Development and Reform Commission has conducted a special inspection of the recent problems reflected by the media, such as the small decline in ticket prices in individual scenic spots and the fact that they have not fallen, requiring all localities to deal with them seriously, respond to social concerns in a timely manner and effectively implement the price reduction in place.
Trade Promotion Bureau to carry out short-and long-term optimization work in an orderly manner
The Macao Trade and Investment Promotion Bureau has submitted a report on the short-and medium-term optimization of "major investment migrants" and "skilled migrants". At present, in addition to stepping up the promotion and implementation of the work in the report, it has been continuously listening to the views of the community and continuously optimizing the content of the report and related work.
The TPA will introduce the relevant optimization work to all sectors of the community as soon as possible.
Of these, five are short-term measures to be implemented this year; five are medium-term measures to be implemented in 2019; and one is long-term measures.
In addition, the Trade Promotion Bureau has conducted a comprehensive review of its internal management system in accordance with the instructions of the Financial Secretary for the Economy, Mr Leung Witt.
The five short-term measures launched this year include:
1. To carry out a review exercise. Priority will be given to reviewing cases that are about to expire for seven years, the cases mentioned in the ICAC report and new renewal cases. If cases of misconduct or signs of wrongdoing are found, they will be referred to the relevant judicial authorities for follow-up on their own initiative;
2. Field inspections of projects involving "major investment migrants". More than 20 investment projects had been inspected by late September;
3. To conduct a comprehensive review of the current evaluation system. Six principles for the analysis of investment projects have been re-established in the evaluation of applications for "major investment migrants". In the evaluation of applications for "skilled migrants", the examination and approval mechanism will be improved by clarifying the elements conducive to the development of Australia and the conditions for the priority absorption of talents. At the same time, a list of "five industries and 10 jobs" with annual priority for the introduction of talents has been drawn up to absorb talents in a more targeted manner in line with the policy direction of the HKSAR Government;
4. To increase the transparency of information, including plans to gradually publish the approval criteria, scoring criteria and proportion from the 4th quarter of this year, and to further refine and make public the approval data;
5. With regard to the improvement of the confirmation mechanism, it has been required to check the work in Australia before confirmation, while major investments must be checked on the spot and financial statements submitted.
The five medium-term measures to be implemented in 2019 include:
1. To establish a mechanism to regularly hear the views of the Commission on Talent Development and the Commission on Economic Development. A working meeting was held with the Commission on Economic Development in September to discuss the establishment of the mechanism.
2. Require the applicant to submit annual financial statements prepared by an independent third party in order to keep under review the operation of the investment project;
3. Further standardize and electronic the process of case application and approval in order to reduce human error;
4. A comprehensive review of the current staffing situation in line with the implementation of a number of optimization measures;
5. Intensify research on the revision of the "Temporary Residence System for Investors, Managers and Specially Qualified Technical Personnel".
As for long-term measures, we will step up the study on the revision of the law. It is expected that the drafting of the relevant regulations will be carried out in the first half of 2019, with a view to completing it as soon as possible, further clarifying the criteria for the examination and approval of temporary residence permits, the review mechanism and the confirmation mechanism, and increasing the investigation function of the Trade Promotion Bureau to more accurately approve and supervise applications for temporary residence permits.
Experts from the national film-free cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities walked into the test field to hear a briefing from the representative of the team of Academician Yu Shuxun of the Chinese Academy of Engineering.
China New Network Xinjiang Shaya September 30 (Geng Dandan Wang Xiaojun) located in Shaya County, Xinjiang, the film-free cotton planting test base, the film-free cotton is growing happily, compared with the mulch cotton next to it "no less", a cluster of snow-white cotton is competing to "open", covered with branches.
From September 27 to 28, the national film-free cotton on-site observation and seminar and exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
At the observation meeting, the reporter learned that the film-free cotton technology system, with "medium cotton 619" and its supporting cultivation measures as the main body, has initially achieved the goal of film-free cultivation in cotton fields, reduced the pollution of the ecological environment and raw cotton by the residual film in cotton fields in Xinjiang, and made significant progress in the research and demonstration of the comprehensive technology of film-free cotton.
Academician Yu Shuxun, a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, a well-known cotton genetic breeder and chief scientist of the cotton system of the National Modern Agricultural Industry Technology System, introduced the growth of film-free cotton to Zhou Guomu, party secretary of Zhejiang Agricultural and Forestry University School.
"The comprehensive technology of film-free cotton we have developed can fully realize the cultivation of cotton without mulch, completely solve the problem of residual film pollution and realize green cotton planting." he said.
Introduction by Yu Shuxun, Academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering.
Xinjiang is the most important cotton-producing area in China. According to the National Bureau of Statistics, the area under cotton cultivation in Xinjiang in 2017 was 35 million mu, accounting for 61% of the country's cotton area.
Since the introduction of mulch into China in 1982, the area of mulch of all kinds of crops in Xinjiang has reached more than 50 million mu, and the annual use of mulch is about 300,000 tons.
Among them, the cotton mulch coverage rate reached 100%, and the cotton field mulch accounted for about 60% of the use of mulch in Xinjiang.
To measure the yield of film-free cotton, the yield of cotton can be 320 kg to 350 kg per mu.
With the increasing input of mulch in Xinjiang, the low recovery rate of residual mulch, the gradual increase in the amount of residual film in the soil, and the destruction of soil structure caused by residual film have seriously affected the sustainable development of agriculture.
The residual film not only causes serious pollution to the soil, but also has a great impact on the quality of cotton fiber.
At present, more than one-third of the cotton fields in Xinjiang have achieved mechanized harvest.
In 2017, the area of machine-picked cotton in Xinjiang was about 14 million mu.
In the process of machine-mining cotton harvest, a large amount of surface income, the broken film on the cotton plant and the broken film adulterated in the original cotton are difficult to remove in the process of raw cotton processing, and cannot be completely removed in the process of follow-up textile processing, seriously affecting the quality of textile products.
On September 28, the national film-free cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
In order to focus on solving mulch pollution in cotton fields, simplifying cotton planting technology and improving the efficiency of cotton fields, Yu Shuxun led his team to implement the "medium cotton 619" film-free cotton technology cultivation over an eight-year period to "add wings" to the green development of agriculture in Xinjiang.
Yu Shu-xun introduced that through innovative new ideas of breeding, a new line of land-based cotton, "medium cotton 619", which is particularly precocious, saline-alkali-resistant, low-temperature-resistant and high-yield, has been bred.
"Under the conditions of film-free cultivation in the southern part of Xinjiang, 'China Cotton 619' has achieved a series of supporting measures, such as film-free sowing machinery, improvement of sowing depth, shallow burial of drip belt under film-free conditions, suitable sowing density screening and reasonable chemical control."
At present, film-free cotton demonstration bases have been set up in Aksu, Kulle, Alar and other places, with a yield of 4,800 kg per hectare.
Planting cotton without film has achieved high yield, cost-saving, environmental protection and comprehensive efficiency.
Zhang Donghai, an agronomist at the Institute of Agricultural Sciences of the Third Division of the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, said that through the research and demonstration of film-free cotton cultivation technology in the past six years, the yield of film-free cotton seed cotton can fully achieve a yield of 320 kg to 350 kg per mu, possibly even higher.
"The popularization of film-free cotton cultivation technology is very promising."
Zhang Donghai believes that at present, film-free cotton cultivation technology can completely solve the problem of soil residual film pollution, but there is still a certain gap in economic benefits compared with mulch cultivation.
"The support of the purchase price of cotton will be conducive to future promotion."
Yu Shu-xun said that the next step, he and his team will continue to carry out in-depth research and large-scale popularization and application of film-free cotton, make the film-free cotton industry bigger and stronger, and completely solve the problem of soil pollution caused by mulch.
