Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi said in a speech to the U.S. Council on Foreign Relations on Friday that China-U.S. relations are once again at a crossroads, and that if the two sides can take a positive and inclusive view of each other, expand and deepen positive cooperation and properly manage differences and contradictions, they can open up better prospects.
