The General Administration of Radio and Television of the Beijing News (reporter Ni Wei) issued the Notice on the Implementation of the Special Regulation of Radio and Television Advertisement on September 29, which will carry out the special regulation of radio and television advertising from this date until the end of this year.
The contents of the remediation include advertisements with vulgar content, style and low grade problems, and medical and health programmes that broadcast problems without record management.
According to the notice, this special remediation work focuses on nine aspects of the search and rectification.
Specifically, they include: advertisements with orientation problems; advertisements with vulgar content, low style and low grade; advertisements with excessive time-out and failure to broadcast problems in accordance with the regulations; advertisements for medical care, drugs, medical devices, health food, cosmetics and beauty with problems such as exaggerating and exaggerating false publicity, misleading the audience, or publishing them in disguised form of programmes, and medical and health-care programmes with problems that have been broadcast without record management; advertisements that exaggerate and exaggerate false publicity, mislead the audience and lure the audience into being deceived; advertisements that have problems such as attracting business, investing in financial management and collectibles with expectations of investment returns; advertisements that induce minors to produce bad behavior or form bad values and harm the physical and mental health of minors;
The remediation work will achieve full coverage throughout the country, and the requirements for remediation and regulation will be fully implemented to the radio and television media at all levels, the frequency of channels, the columns and periods of programmes, and "there will be no blind areas, no dead corners and no exceptions".
The notice requires the administrative departments of radio and television at all levels to deal with all kinds of illegal and illegal advertisements found in the course of supervision and inspection in strict accordance with the Measures for the Handling of Violations by Radio and Television Broadcast Agencies of the General Administration.
If the circumstances of the violation are serious, they shall be dealt with seriously, such as admonition, notification of criticism, suspension of the broadcast of advertisements until the suspension of the broadcast of frequency channels, and shall be publicly exposed to the public as appropriate.
In recent years, the General Administration of Radio and Television has repeatedly called a halt to illegal advertisements.
This year, the State Administration of Radio and Television issued a notice publicly calling for the suspension of advertisements for serious violations such as "0-bubble fruit milk", "Sharva Cocktail" and "Bonrette Plant Anti-Breeding Hair Dew", which have orientation deviations and exaggerated publicity and misled the audience.
The General Administration of Radio, Radio and Television has formulated a number of regulations and notices to regulate the broadcast of advertisements on radio and television.
The Notice on Further Strengthening the Administration of Advertisements for the Broadcasting of Television Shopping Short Film by TV Channel stipulates that television channels shall not broadcast advertisements for television shopping short films between 18:00 and 24:00 a day.
When advertisements for short television shopping films are broadcast at other times, the moderator shall not be used for publicity, the "hawking" exaggerated voice, intonation and movement shall not be used for publicity, the "orthopaedic", "plastic", "fat-penetrating" and "fat-throwing" shall not be used for publicity or disguised publicity of breast enhancement and weight loss products, and no more than one (second) advertisement for short television shopping clips shall be broadcast every hour every day, each of which shall not exceed three minutes.
The Circular on Further Strengthening the Administration of the Broadcasting of Radio and Television Advertisements stipulates that when placing advertisements in the middle of film and television dramas, television stations must strictly abide by the provisions of Order No. 61 of the General Administration: two commercial advertisements may be placed in each episode (in 45 minutes) during non-prime time, each time not exceeding 1 minute and 30 seconds; one commercial advertisement may be placed in each episode during prime time (19:00 to 21:00) for a period of not more than one minute; and the length of the advertisement shall be prompted when placing advertisements.
The notice also stipulates that radio and television broadcasting institutions shall strictly examine the qualifications and certificates of health information advertisements such as medical care, medicines, medical devices and health food, and resolutely prohibit the broadcast of sex-related advertisements.
We should standardize the form of health information advertising, and should not publish advertisements in disguised form in the form of health information special programs.
Special programmes on health information shall focus on the introduction of scientific knowledge such as disease prevention, control and treatment, shall not contain advertising content such as medical care, drugs, medical devices and health food, and shall not be certified in the name of patients and doctors, pharmacists and experts.
