China News Agency, Fuzhou, September 30 (reporter Long Min) The 6th meeting of the Standing Committee of the 13th National People's Congress of Fujian Province voted on the 30th to adopt the Regulations on the Promotion of the Construction of Ecological Civilization in Fujian Province.
"Green Water Qingshan is Jinshan Yinshan" was written into the legislation of Fujian Province for the first time, running through the whole regulation, becoming an operational and enforceable regulation.
Fujian is China's first national test area for ecological civilization.
The head of the Legal Affairs Office of the People's Government of Fujian Province said that it was necessary and urgent to form a basic regulation on the construction of ecological civilization from the whole and the overall situation in order to solve the problem of regulating the construction of ecological civilization by decentralized regulations, regulations and policy documents alone, as well as to provide a legal basis for the formulation and promulgation of relevant regulations, normative documents and measures.
The Regulations fully reflect the characteristics of Fujian, and translate the mature experience and practices in the practice of the construction of ecological civilization into the form of regulations and regulations for popularization and implementation: for example, the replicable and popularized "Changting Experience" formed by the work of soil and water conservation in Fujian Province, the Regulations summarize and enhance the experience of soil and water conservation in Fujian Province, stipulate that local people's governments at or above the county level shall strengthen their unified leadership in the work of soil and water conservation, delimit key prevention areas and control areas for soil erosion on the basis of the results of soil erosion investigations; and, for example, the river length system, the regulations, which originated in Fujian Province, shall raise the river length system and the lake length system to the legislative level, and stipulate that the local people's governments at all levels shall fully implement the river length system and the lake length system.
The regulation provides for the implementation of a lifelong inquiry system for liability for ecological and environmental damage.
Whoever, in violation of the requirements of scientific development, causes serious damage to ecological and environmental resources shall be held accountable for life to the main leading cadres and relevant persons in charge who bear the leadership responsibility.
According to the report, the Regulations on the Promotion of the Construction of Ecological Civilization in Fujian Province will come into force on November 1 this year.
China and Pakistan agree to complete the construction of the economic corridor in a timely manner and speed up the construction of the port of Guadar
China and Pakistan have agreed to further consolidate and expand economic relations between the two countries, China's foreign ministry said Sunday.
China and Pakistan issued a joint statement Sunday to further strengthen their strategic partnership.
The two sides reiterated their "commitment to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor" and "oppose negative propaganda against the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor".
China and Pakistan will "strengthen practical cooperation in the field of trade and investment and enhance Pakistan's industrial capacity by setting up joint ventures in priority areas, transferring labor-intensive industries and developing cooperation among small and medium-sized enterprises," Reuters quoted China's foreign ministry as saying.
According to a press release published on the website of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the two sides agreed to complete the projects under construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor in a timely manner, speed up the construction of the port and supporting projects in the port of Guadar, focus on economic and social development, create jobs and improve people's livelihood, and accelerate cooperation in the fields of industry, parks and agriculture.
"The two sides also agreed to complete the second phase of the negotiations on the China-Pakistan Free Trade Agreement as soon as possible and to continue to promote the negotiations on the China-Pakistan Trade in Services Agreement." he said.
In a joint statement signed on Sunday, the two sides reiterated their commitment to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor and agreed that the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor is a win-win plan for cooperation that will promote regional connectivity and bring prosperity and development to the region as a whole.
The two sides agreed that the port of Guadar is an important node for cross-regional connectivity and a pillar of the China-Pakistan economic corridor.
The two sides agreed to speed up the construction of the port and supporting projects at the port of Guadar.
China and Pakistan also said in a joint statement that they opposed negative propaganda against the China-Pakistan economic corridor.
The two sides agreed to establish a strategic dialogue between the foreign ministers of China and Pakistan and to adjust the original strategic dialogue at the level of deputy foreign ministers to diplomatic consultations.
In addition, the two countries will further strengthen defense cooperation and maintain high-level visits between the two militaries and exchanges between various departments and levels.
In order to further encourage overseas investors to invest in China, four ministries, including the Ministry of Finance of China, jointly announced that, with effect from January 1, 2018, the scope of application of the policy of not collecting advance income tax for domestic direct investment for the profits allocated by overseas investors from resident enterprises in China will be expanded from foreign investment incentive projects to all projects and areas that are not prohibited from foreign investment.
According to a notice published on the website of the Ministry of Finance, the suspension of advance income tax by overseas investors must meet several conditions at the same time, including direct investment by overseas investors with profits, including equity investment such as capital increase, new construction and equity acquisition by overseas investors with profits, but excluding the addition, transfer and acquisition of shares of listed companies (except eligible strategic investment).
It also includes that the profits earned by overseas investors belong to the equity investment income such as dividends and dividends formed by the actual distribution of the retained income already realized by Chinese resident enterprises to investors.
If the profits used by overseas investors for direct investment are paid in the form of cash, the relevant funds shall be transferred directly from the account of the profit distribution enterprise to the account of the invested enterprise or the assignor of equity, and shall not be turned around in other accounts inside and outside the country before the direct investment; if the profits used by overseas investors for direct investment are paid in non-cash forms such as physical objects and securities, the ownership of the relevant assets shall be transferred directly from the profit distribution enterprise to the invested enterprise or the assignor of equity, and shall not be held or temporarily held by other enterprises or individuals before the direct investment.
The notice states that overseas investors actually recover their direct investment that enjoys the treatment of the policy of not collecting income tax in advance through the transfer of equity, repurchase and liquidation, and, within 7 days after the actual collection of the corresponding funds, declare to the tax authorities the payment of the deferred tax in accordance with the prescribed procedures.
In order to encourage overseas investors to continue to invest and operate in China, four ministries, including the Ministry of Finance and the Ministry of Commerce of China, jointly issued a notice at the end of 2017 that, with effect from January 1, 2017, the profits allocated by overseas investors from resident enterprises in China will be invested directly in incentive investment projects, and if the prescribed conditions are met, a deferred tax policy will be implemented and no advance income tax will be levied for the time being.
The executive meeting of the State Council of China decided last week to expand the scope of application of the temporary non-collection of advance income tax on foreign reinvestment from incentive foreign-funded projects to all non-prohibited projects and fields, and further strengthen the protection of intellectual property rights.
The reporter learned from the National Health and Health Commission that, compared with decades ago, the incidence of malnutrition among children and adolescents in China has declined, while the incidence of overweight and obesity has increased significantly.
In this regard, experts pointed out that the most important concept of maintaining a healthy weight is to "cure the disease", vigorously promote scientific fitness and a reasonable diet.
According to the "Core Information and Interpretation of Health Education for Young People in China (2018 Edition)" recently released by the National Health and Health Commission, the key to maintaining a healthy weight is a reasonable diet and scientific exercise.
Overweight, obesity and blind weight loss are all bad for your health.
The health hidden dangers behind the "little chubby pier" cannot be ignored.
Ding Gang-qiang, director of the Institute of Nutrition and Health of the China Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, said overweight obesity is harmful to the normal growth and development of young people, has a negative impact on their psychology, behavior, cognition and intelligence, and can even lead to high blood pressure, high blood sugar and high blood lipid in children.
At the same time, overweight and obesity in teenagers are prone to continue into adulthood, which will increase the risk of chronic diseases such as high blood pressure and diabetes in adulthood.
Ding Gang-qiang said tests on the nutrition and health of Chinese residents in 2010-2012 showed that the rate of overweight among children and adolescents aged 6-17 in China was 9.6% and the rate of obesity was 6.4%, adding up to 16%.
At the same time, overweight and obesity among children and adolescents is characterized by higher boys than girls and higher in cities than in rural areas, and the rate of overweight and obesity has increased significantly in recent decades.
How do teenagers cope with overweight and obesity?
Zhang Li, deputy director of the Center for Scientific Fitness and Health Promotion of the State General Administration of Sports, pointed out that the main causes of obesity among young people are excessive calorie intake and insufficient physical activity.
For this simple obesity, attention should be paid to scientific exercise and reasonable diet control.
Zhang pointed out that the most important concept of maintaining a healthy weight is to "cure the disease". One of the most important elements is to provide all-round science education to schools, parents and students, popularize the dangers of overweight and obesity, and raise young people's awareness of prevention.
Adolescents should undergo regular medical examinations, monitor growth and development indicators such as height and weight, detect early and scientifically judge whether there are overweight and obesity problems, so as to take timely intervention measures.
For young people who are already overweight and obese, Ding Gang-qiang suggested that, in addition to actively and scientifically arranging meals and exercise, young people are at a special physiological stage. They should avoid the use of hunger or semi-hunger therapy to control and lose weight, and should not take weight-loss drugs blindly.
Sept 28 (Reuters) -Facebook (FB.O) said on Friday that hackers stole digital landing code, giving them access to nearly 50 million user accounts, unprecedented in scope and the worst security breach in its history.
Facebook, which has more than 2.2 billion monthly users, said it had not yet determined whether the attacker misused any accounts or stole personal information.
The company also did not find the location of the hackers and was not sure whether the hackers targeted specific victims.
Its preliminary analysis showed that it was a large-scale attack.
In a media conference call, Chief Executive Zuckerberg called the incident "really serious".
A spokesman for the company said his account, as well as that of operations chief Sheryl Sandberg, were also affected.
Facebook shares fell 2.6% on Friday, dragging down major Wall Street stock indexes.
U.S. lawmakers said Friday that the attack could increase calls for data privacy legislation.
"This is yet another sad evidence that Congress needs to take action to protect the privacy and safety of social media users," Democratic Senator Mark Warner said in a statement.
'I hope to get an answer to Reuters' report on the security breach, 'Rohit Chopra, a member of the Federal Trade Commission (FTC), said on Twitter.
China New Network Changsha September 30 (Zheng Yu Liang Tian Chan) September 30 is China's 5th martyrs' anniversary.
On such a special day, people from all walks of life, such as the families of Hunan Anti-Japanese War veterans, representatives of PNG Party members and representatives of Hunan Veterans' Home, came to the "Tang People's Wanshou Garden Anti-Japanese War Theme Park" in Changsha City to participate in the collective burial ceremony of Hunan Anti-Japanese War veterans on the 2018 Martyrs' Day, and to see off the partners of 10 Anti-Japanese War veterans and four Anti-Japanese War veterans.
"The veterans of the Anti-Japanese War are witnesses of China's Anti-Japanese War and are real, vivid and distinctive teaching materials for patriotism."
Liu Xiao, former vice-chairman of the Hunan Provincial Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said that the patriotism of the veterans of the Anti-Japanese War, who were brave and fearless, was a valuable spiritual treasure for the contemporary Chinese people.
In his speech, Zhu Jianjun, Vice-Chairman of the Changsha Municipal Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) and Chairman of the Changsha Municipal Committee of the People's Republic of China, pointed out that in recent years, the "Care for Veterans of the Anti-Japanese War" project has become an excellent brand in the social service work of the Changsha Municipal People's Republic of China by providing care services to veterans of the Anti-Japanese War through living allowances, free old-age pension and free burial.
He believes that only if history is engraved in the heart can the spirit of the Anti-Japanese War be passed on.
