China News Agency, Yichang, October 1 (Guo Xiaoying Liu Min) The newly revised Regulations on Navigation Dispatch of the Three Gorges-Gezhouba Water Conservancy Hub (hereinafter referred to as the "Dispatch Rules ") were officially implemented on October 1. After two years of trial navigation, the Three Gorges ship lift was officially dispatched in a unified manner with the lock.
On the first day of the implementation of the new regulations, the navigation order in the waters of the Three Gorges-Gezhouba was good.
The Three Gorges Navigation Administration of the Yangtze River issued its first security plan at 2100 hours on September 30 and conducted security checks on 160 ships, with a total of 124 ships passing the security checks.
At 1400 hours on 1 October, the navigation department arranged the first crossing plan after the implementation of the new regulations.
After the implementation of the new regulations, the security plan will be issued once a day at 9: 00pm and 21: 00pm each, and the dam crossing plan will be issued once a day at 14: 00pm and 20: 00pm each to facilitate the flexible arrangement of the dam crossing plan by ships.
The Dispatch Regulations add the principle of "classification control" for the dispatching of ships over the dam, clarify the priority order of ships crossing the dam according to the functional positioning of the lock and the ship lift respectively, and adjust the short-term passenger ships crossing the lock to the same priority level as the demonstration ship and the integrity ship.
This is also the second anniversary of the trial operation of the lift, the official unified dispatching with the lock.
And the Sichuan River and the Three Gorges Reservoir area large long and wide demonstration ships, new energy power ships are also in the priority level for the first time.
At the same time, the Dispatch Regulations adjust the "navigation dispatching management waters" from the previous 180 km of near-dam waters to 541.8 km of water from the Yuanyang Yangtze River Bridge to the Shishou Yangtze River Bridge, and divide "core waters, near-dam waters, control waters and dispatching waters".
This is conducive to the ship's choice of suitable waters for the sluice, reducing the backlog of ships in the dam area.
The Dispatch Regulations also, in accordance with the current characteristics of ships crossing dams and waiting for sluice, put forward integrity control measures such as the cancellation of the declaration of ships that violate the law and the 24-hour delay in crossing the dam.
After the Three Gorges Reservoir, the navigation conditions in the reservoir area have been improved, promoting the rapid development of Yangtze River shipping.
According to the data, the annual cargo pass of the Three Gorges Lock and the Gezhouba Lock increased from 34.3 million tons in 2004 to 138 million tons and 140 million tons in 2017, respectively.
In the past two years, the Three Gorges ship-lift has passed through 5,767 ships, with 162,200 passengers and a cargo volume of 1.728 million tons.
Chen Dong-yuan, deputy director of the Three Gorges Navigation Administration, said the Dispatch Regulations play a positive role in promoting the management of good faith crossing the gate, maintaining the navigation order of the two dam hubs, unlocking the pressure on ships in the dam area and enhancing the navigation capacity.
