Qingdao, Oct 1 (Xinhua) -- Affected by Typhoon Tam Mei, the 2018 International Limit Sailing Series Qingdao Station "Mazelun Cup", which was scheduled to open on September 30, postponed its first race day until October 1, and held a pre-match meeting at the Qingdao Olympic Sailing Center before the match. All 12 water-wing double-body sailing team captains from six countries and regions appeared.
As a result of the sound of Typhoon Tam Mei, strong winds continued in the Hong Kong pool, with a maximum wind speed of up to 24 knots. The departure signal was delayed by nearly 90 minutes from 1pm on the 30th. The wind speed was still not reduced. The tournament's chief referee, Anne Mudrand, announced the cancellation of the first day of the match and the postponement of the match until the afternoon of October 1.
"The strong winds from the shore continued, and the sea conditions were too intense."
"In this case, no one knows when and with what wind the gusts are blowing towards the racing boat," Mudrand explained.
Close to the city, in the current wind conditions, cancelling the game is the smartest choice. "
There was still some disappointment for all the ready crew.
"The race boat is ready to stop and we are in good shape."
Qingdao's helmsman, Max Richardson, admitted: "But I know the rescheduling of the race is the right choice, and I hope the wind is smaller today and we can show our hand."
"The loss of a day makes the game more interesting," said Omika Wilkinson, the "star of hope" known as the New Zealand team for the 2020 Tokyo Olympics.
Because the weight of today's game will increase, and there are only two days left to play.
Everyone's going to be particularly desperate. '
Despite the strong sea breeze, Pierre Ives Durand, the helmsman of the French ABM team, appealed at a pre-match meeting about his warm past with Qingdao, where the competition was held: five years ago, the International Limit Sailing Series suffered an accidental injury and a broken muscle, and thanks to the handling of the local event's medical team, he was able to stand at the venue five years later.
It is reported that the International Limit Sailing Series was founded in 2007 and is known as the World Sailing League with Volvo, the Copa America and the World Sailing Challenge Tour.
The Qingdao Station competition will use the "Flying Ghost" water-wing two-body sail.
2018 marks the 8th year that the event has landed in Qingdao, the "sailing capital," and Qingdao Station is also the closing battle for the series.
Despite the continued turmoil in global financial markets, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority said on Monday that investment income from foreign exchange funds fell 97% annually in the third quarter of this year, but better than in the previous quarter, as overseas stocks rose and foreign exchange losses narrowed significantly under the China-US trade war.
According to the latest data from the HKMA, the Exchange Fund recorded investment income of HK US $1.6 billion in July-September 2018, down sharply from HK US $61.8 billion in the same period last year, but better than the revised HK US $100 million in the second quarter of this year.
Speaking in the Legislative Council, HKMA President Mr Chan Tak-lin said that at the beginning of the China-US trade war, Hong Kong and emerging market stock indexes ran counter to the US stock index. Until the end of September and after the US stock index peaked in early October, market sentiment began to reverse as investors gradually realized that the trade war was also bad for the US itself.
"It is a good thing that there is a change in market sentiment, and if a trade war has only a unilateral impact, it will not help solve things." he said.
But he also pointed out that "if the trade war between China and the United States is not resolved, financial market volatility will continue to rise."
In the third quarter of this year, the Exchange Fund's stock investment losses in Hong Kong narrowed by 8% to HK $4.7 billion from the previous quarter, while overseas stock investment earnings rose 172% to HK $12.8 billion. Foreign exchange losses of HK $16.2 billion and bond earnings of HK $9.7 billion, down 24% and 31% on a quarterly basis, respectively, mainly reflecting a general rise in the US dollar against major currencies during the quarter and a rise in the US yield rate of 3% in mid-September.
The Exchange Fund is mainly used to support the Hong Kong dollar.
Hong Kong has implemented a linked exchange rate system between the Hong Kong dollar and the US dollar since 1983.
As for the current financial situation in Hong Kong, Mr Chan said that uncertainty in the economic and asset markets had increased and downside risks had increased, but that Hong Kong's financial system was sound, defensive and earthquake-resistant.
"Hong Kong has a rich international investment position, with an external net worth of US $1.4 trillion equivalent to four times GDP, 2.5 times higher than Singapore's and 0.6 times Japan's, and it is more than enough to cope with the downward cycle or reversal of the economy." he said.
Recently, the Hong Kong dollar's interest rate has continued to fall and the spread with the US dollar has widened. Mr Chan pointed out that the Hong Kong dollar's exchange rate had risen by more than 400 basis points on 21 September. It was widely believed that it was mainly related to the rise in the Hong Kong dollar's interest rate. Since then, the Hong Kong dollar has hovered around 7.80-7.84 against the US dollar. In the recent past, the Hong Kong dollar's interest rate has continued to fall and the spread with the US dollar has widened, which may attract the market to sell Hong Kong dollars and buy US dollars, making the Hong Kong dollar more likely to trigger a weak exchange guarantee again than in the previous period.
But he believes the situation of Hong Kong dollar interest rates below the US dollar rate will change in the future as the Bank of Hong Kong's rate hike cycle begins and the normalization of Hong Kong dollar interest rates is under way.
"The Hong Kong dollar interest rate will be more in line with the US dollar interest rate, and we must be more careful to manage risks and be prepared to cope with market fluctuations." he said.
The three-month interest rate fell 0.9% to 2.08179% on Monday, widening the spread with the US dollar from 46 basis points to 51 basis points, while the one-month interest rate hit a five-month low, widening the spread with the US dollar from 120 basis points to 127 basis points.
From May to mid-September, the spot exchange rate of the Hong Kong dollar was close to 7.85 to the US dollar for most of the time.
During the period, the weak-party exchange guarantee was triggered several times in May and August, after it was first triggered in April, due to factors such as the outflow of some of the funds from the prospectus from the Hong Kong dollar after the end of the arbitrage campaign and the large-scale prospectus.
The HKMA buys Hong Kong dollars and sells US dollars at the 7.85 level in accordance with the linked exchange rate system to maintain the stability of the Hong Kong dollar.
The HKMA bought about HK US $52.1 billion in May and August under the Weak-side Exchange Guarantee Mechanism.
Does the new tax law still have preferential treatment for overseas people?
In response to a reporter's question on the 30th, the relevant officials of the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation said that in order to maintain policy stability, the next step in the implementation of the new personal income tax law will be to consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for overseas people, including those from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
A reporter asked, the newly revised personal income tax law has adjusted the judgment standard for individual income tax residents in China from one year to 183 days.
In the next step in the implementation of the Law, are there any preferential arrangements for overseas people, including those from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan?
In response, the person-in-charge said that the current regulations on the implementation of the personal income tax law have special preferential provisions on the issue of tax payment for overseas people. Individuals who have no domicile in China but have resided for more than one year but less than five years may pay personal income tax only on the part paid by units or individuals within China for their income derived from outside China.
The person in charge said that in order to maintain policy stability, the next step in the implementation of the new personal income tax law will be to consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for overseas people, including those from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
There is no "threshold" moon center: quality certification promotes quality improvement.
With the pull of the "two-child economy" and the prosperity of the mother-and-child market, from the north to the third-and 4th-tier cities, various grades of moon clubhouses have sprung up in various places.
The current hot moon clubhouse has met the consumer needs of the masses, with fees ranging from tens of thousands of yuan to hundreds of thousands of yuan, but it is also in an awkward position. The agency has no threshold so far and there is still a gap in supervision.
The State Administration of Market Supervision recently launched a series of activities for the 2018 National "Quality Month". The reporter came to a five-star moon center in Tianjin to visit the certification experience of maternal and child care services.
The general moon center provides neonatal care, nutrition meals, postpartum repair plastic shape and other services.
In this moon center, the reporter saw that nurses check the breastfeeding of newborns every day, and professional nursing workers provide fine care services such as bathing and touching for newborns.
At the same time, in order to meet the needs of new mothers, from wound care in the early stages of the moon to beauty care in the middle and late stages of the moon, nursing projects such as Chinese medicine treatment and beauty are provided to help mothers regain their fair figure.
A new mother who lives told reporters that she had only booked for the moon club eight months in advance.
The service items of the moon clubhouse directly affect the comfort and physical recovery of the mother during the month. Some small moon clubhouses can only provide some simple moon services. There are hidden dangers such as irregular disinfection and hygiene, easy cross-infection, and unscientific diet.
The head of the moon center said they were the only one of all five-star moon centers in Tianjin to be certified for B-level services.
"Although some customers did not understand the meaning of B-level certification at first, it is of great significance to the long-term development of the enterprise to force companies to strictly standardize process management through certification to benefit customers." he said.
Pan Lifen, deputy director of the Certification and Supervision Department of the State Administration of Market Supervision, said that service certification is a new type of certification system based on customer perception, paying attention to organizational quality management and the satisfaction of service characteristics. It is an important part of the national quality infrastructure and plays a positive role in increasing the proportion of high-quality service supply and enhancing the international competitiveness of China's services.
Since 2004, after more than 10 years of development, the service certification project has gone through a process of gradual development from scratch, and a number of influential service certification, such as financial service certification, mother-and-child care service certification, commodity after-sales service certification, e-commerce service certification and health service certification, have emerged.
According to statistics from the State Administration of Market Supervision, there are more than 130 service certification institutions in China, more than 2,000 service certification personnel and nearly 8,000 valid certification certificates.
Mr Pan said the development of service certification should be further guided and promoted, the coverage of service certification should be gradually expanded in the fields of health, education, sports, finance and electricity business, and the supply-side reform and quality improvement of the service industry should be promoted.
HONG KONG, Nov 5 (Reuters) -Hong Kong property prices have fallen for two months in a row after peaking, with the head of the Hong Kong Monetary Authority, Mr Chan Tak-lin, saying on Monday that it would take time to see if the property market had entered a downward cycle and that if confirmed, consideration could be given to easing the tightening of counter-cyclical measures at an appropriate time.
Mr Chan also said that if property prices were to be revised back, it would be those who bought property at the peak of the property market who would be the first to be affected. However, it was expected that there would be a sharp fall in property prices, such as during the 1997 Asian financial crisis, and that the chances of the public selling property at a significant price reduction would be much lower.
Speaking at the Legislative Council briefing, Mr Chan, who led a number of senior HKMA officials, said that if it was confirmed that the property market had entered a downward cycle, the measures could be relaxed as appropriate.
"However, only a few weeks of data have been seen, and it is still too early to relax, and it will take more time to see if the property market is entering a downward cycle." he said.
Since October 2009, the HKMA has so far introduced eight rounds of counter-cyclical measures to significantly tighten mortgages for all types of properties, including reducing the number of mortgages and requiring mortgage applicants to pass rigorous stress tests to enhance banks' risk management and earthquake-resistant capacity.
As Hong Kong officially entered a cycle of interest rate hikes, the Hong Kong private residential price index peaked for two consecutive months in August-September, with the monthly decline widening to 1.44% in September.
But the cumulative increase in the first three quarters of this year was still 10.2%.
According to the HKMA, the financial situation of households that measure Hong Kong's earthquake-resistant ability to face financial risks remains healthy. In the second quarter of this year, the proportion of self-occupied households without a mortgage in Hong Kong reached 66%, higher than the average of 60% in 2009-11. The average number of new mortgages granted and the contribution-to-income ratio of new mortgages granted were 47% and 34% respectively, a marked improvement from 64% and 41% respectively in 2009-11.
But Mr Chan said the high earthquake-resistant capacity did not mean that people who had already bought a home would not be damaged by the economic downturn, as property valuations would fall and those who bought a building during the peak period would bear the brunt.
Although the HKMA has tightened bank lending to mortgage lenders, home buyers can also obtain a high number of mortgage loans through mortgage insurance or mortgage loans provided by developers.
Mr Chan said that at present, together with the mortgage loans provided to developers, the number of mortgages for borrowers could reach 85-90%. If the price of the property fell by 10%, there would be negative assets (i.e. the market value of the property fell below the total amount of outstanding mortgage loans).
However, the Vice-President of the HKMA, Mr Nguyen Kwok-heng, pointed out that the authorities estimated that the total number of mortgages provided by developers was only 2-2.5% of the total number of bank mortgages, which was still low.
At the peak of negative assets in Hong Kong in 2003, the number of negative assets exceeded 100,000, accounting for 22% of building suppliers.
As of the third quarter of this year, Hong Kong had recorded zero negative assets in seven consecutive quarters.
BEIJING, Oct 1 (Xinhua) -- E-commerce retail export enterprises welcomed another wave of positive tax burden on October 1, involving value-added tax and excise tax exemption.
The Ministry of Finance, the State Administration of Taxation, the Ministry of Commerce and the General Administration of Customs have jointly issued a letter making it clear that if electric export enterprises in the comprehensive test area of cross-border e-commerce export goods that have not obtained a valid purchase certificate, and meet the following conditions, they shall try out the tax-free policy of value-added tax and excise tax.
First, e-commerce export enterprises are registered in the comprehensive test area and register the date of export, the name of the goods, the unit of measurement, the quantity, the unit price and the amount on the integrated service platform on the cross-border e-commerce line at the place of registration.
Second, the export goods go through the e-commerce export declaration procedures through the customs in the place where the comprehensive test area is located.
Third, the export goods do not belong to the goods that the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation, in accordance with the decision of the State Council, explicitly cancel the export tax rebate (exemption).
The notice makes it clear that the General Administration of Customs regularly transmits electronic information on the declaration list of e-commerce export commodities to the State Administration of Taxation.
The tax authorities of the comprehensive test areas shall strengthen the tax-free administration of export goods in accordance with the electronic information on the declaration list of export commodities cleared by the State Administration of Taxation.
The notice points out that the specific measures for the administration of tax exemption shall be formulated by the provincial tax departments in consultation with the financial and commercial departments.
The offices of the leading groups for the construction of the comprehensive test areas and the competent commercial departments should promote communication and cooperation between departments and the implementation of relevant policies in an integrated manner, accelerate the establishment of a statistical monitoring system for e-commerce exports, and promote the healthy and rapid development of cross-border e-commerce.
Ordos, Nov 5 (Zhang Linhu) A man in Liaoning Province killed his lover and threw his body and then absconded to the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region because of a disagreement over the distribution of money.
On the 5th, the reporter learned from the Dongsheng District Public Security Bureau of Ordos City, Inner Mongolia, that after a joint investigation by the police of the two places, the man was successfully captured.
On June 26, 2018, a woman went missing in Anshan City, Liaoning Province, and her family alerted local police.
After the police investigation and investigation, this is not a simple case of missing people, the missing person Bai Mou is likely to be killed by his lover Wang Mou, the police immediately set up a special case team to carry out further investigation.
On October 30, the special case team found that the suspect, Wang Mou, may have been hiding in Dongsheng District of Ordos City. The Dongsheng police immediately organized a competent police force to cooperate fully with the Liaoning police in the investigation of the case.
After five days of investigation, the police finally found out Wang Mou's landing point, and carried out a detailed combing of his relationship.
On November 4, the police of the two places joined forces to capture the suspect, Wang Mou, in a digging machine parts shop in Dongsheng District.
According to Wang Mou, he and the victim, Bai Mou, are lovers, because Bai Mou's sister has a large amount of money in Bai Mou's name for the time being, the two decided to take the money as their own.
On June 22, 2018, Wang Mou and Bai Mou were at odds over the use of the funds, Wang Mou then killed Bai Mou in a rented house, decomposing the body and throwing the body.
At present, the suspect Wang Mou has been handed over to the Liaoning Anshan police.
