SHENZHEN, Oct 1 (Zheng Xiaohong Xu Dian-wei Liu Shu-meng) On October 1, the first day of the "Golden Week" of the National Day of the Mainland and the last day of the National Day public holiday in Hong Kong, many Mainland residents took advantage of their holidays to go out of the country to play and shop. Many Hong Kong residents who came to Shenzhen returned to Hong Kong on the same day. There was a "explosion" of passenger flow at various ports in Shenzhen. Twenty-two new self-help channels were opened at the Luohu and Shenzhen Bay ports to enhance the efficiency of customs clearance at the ports and facilitate efficient and efficient customs clearance for passengers.
According to the data provided by the Shenzhen Border Inspection Station, as of 16:00 p.m. on the same day, the number of people entering and leaving the Shenzhen Port had reached more than 429,000, and the number of means of transport had reached more than 168,000 (ships, frames and columns). The ports had always been busy and unruly, maintaining good entry and exit order.
It is understood that due to a number of positive factors, such as the increase in the number of countries providing exit visa-free policies for Chinese citizens, the number of passengers using the National Day holiday to travel to Europe and Southeast Asia for holiday shopping has continued to increase.
On the morning of the first day, the exit direction of Luohu, Shenzhen Bay, Huanggang, Fukuda and other ports welcomed the peak passenger (car) flow. Among them, the peak passenger flow at Luohu Port lasted from 9:00 a.m. to 11:00 a.m. and the peak passenger (car) flow at Shenzhen Bay Port was from 6:30 a.m. to 13:00 noon.
According to the report, in order to cope with the peak flow of passengers (vehicles) entering and leaving the country, the Shenzhen Border Inspection Station, in accordance with the unified deployment of the State Administration of Immigration, has launched the peak-hour service model of passenger (vehicle) flow, arranged for overtime police to support the front line of duty, opened full inspection channels in advance, guided passengers and vehicles to wait for inspection in an orderly manner, ensured that Chinese citizens are queuing for entry and exit customs clearance for no more than 30 minutes, while taking into account the efficiency of customs clearance for foreigners, and strengthened the maintenance of order in densely populated areas to ensure the safety and order of customs clearance.
At the same time, the Shenzhen Border Inspection Station reminds passengers entering and leaving the country to pay attention to the validity period of documents, visas and signings before travelling, arrange their trips rationally, avoid the peak hours of passenger flow as far as possible, and choose the right time and the right port to travel.
Passengers travelling to Hong Kong on the Guangzhou-Shenzhen-Hong Kong high-speed rail line are required to hold valid entry and exit documents and visa endorsement. High-speed rail tickets are only bus vouchers and cannot be used as entry and exit documents. If they are unable to leave the country for Hong Kong for reasons such as non-conformity of the documents, they should follow the guidelines of the Border Inspection Police and wait at a designated place for the staff of the MTR Corporation to take them to the Mainland for the ride.
Systemic lupus erythematosus is a chronic disease that involves multiple organs throughout the body and has been considered an "incurable disease" in the past.
Because its pathogenesis is unknown, diagnosis and treatment is difficult, lack of effective treatment methods and can not be cured.
Recently, a joint team of Liu Wanli, a researcher at Tsinghua University's School of Life Sciences, and Chiu Zhanguo, director of the Rheumatic Immunization Center at Peking University People's Hospital, found a molecular mutation in human immunoglobulin that increases the susceptibility of systemic lupus erythematosus, and that the mutation is involved in regulating immune B cells.
In short, the two teams confirmed that an abnormal immune molecule in the human body is a major cause of systemic lupus erythematosus.
According to Sun Xiaolin, one of the authors of the article and the People's Hospital of Peking University, the Chiu Zhanguo team collected nearly 2,000 large samples of patients with systemic lupus erythematosus and conducted a study, and found that patients with immunoglobulin variants had produced pathogenic cells and a wide variety and large number of autoantibodies, and that the incidence and severity of inflammation such as nephritis, arthritis, serositis and vasculitis had increased significantly.
Through a variety of research methods, such as immune cell tracer, animal tests and sequencing, Liu Wanli's team found the immune signal pathway activated by immune molecular variation, which promotes the pathogenic mechanism of B cells secreting a variety of self-antibodies.
The reporter learned that the two teams are strong and strong, give full play to their respective advantages, and realize the close combination of basic research and clinical application.
Liu Wanli's team is committed to the study of B-lymphocyte immune identification and immune activation, while the Chiu Zhanguo team has long been engaged in the clinical study of systemic lupus erythematosus.
"This study is one of the results of many years of cooperation between the two teams and is the first time that the academic community has recognized that immunoglobulin genetic abnormalities will induce systemic lupus erythematosus, laying a solid foundation for further academic research and clinical targeted treatment." he said.
This is not short-term, but in accordance with the law.
A lawyer goes to court with an axe?
The news was really exciting at first glance, and it blew up in the legal circle.
Zhongfa, Quanzhou City, Fujian Province, then fined the lawyer 500 yuan and recommended in writing that the Quanzhou Bar Association investigate and deal with it.
According to the Beijing News, the Quanzhou Law Association issued an official notice saying that the actions of the two lawyers did not involve violations of the law and would not be punished in accordance with the law.
According to many reports, the treatment of the Quanzhou Law Association is not short-term or confrontational, but has been approved by the Quanzhou Central Court.
An incident that could have caused tension within the legal community was finally properly resolved.
The reversal of the matter stems from a more complete restoration of the truth: the axe carried by the lawyer involved is of the same style and model as the defendant's murder weapon, but it is not open-edged, only as auxiliary evidence in the examination of evidence, and there is no subjective intention to intimidate or "endanger the safety of the court".
There are four very important details to pay attention to in judging whether the actions of the lawyer involved are illegal and illegal: first, the local court has held two previous sessions, showing only photos of the axe, and from a defence point of view, it is necessary to show the original object of the axe; second, the axe was purchased only an hour before the court session, not because the lawyer did not want to seek the consent of the judge, but objectively failed to contact the judge; third, the whole axe was not used too much or improperly; and 4th, the lawyer involved publicly apologized to the court for the first time.
Combined with these circumstances, it can be seen that the lawyer involved "appeared in court with an axe" had nothing to do with evil, but only for the purpose of defence.
After clarifying the whole fact, the Quanzhou Law Association did not push the boat, but resisted the pressure to make the decision not to punish.
And this decision, also can stand the test of facts and law.
As for bringing the axe, which is used as a control tool, to court without the permission of the court, it is indeed easy to cause unease and misunderstanding.
For reasons of safety and caution, the Quanzhou Central Court's previous fine penalties and judicial recommendations are also not unreasonable.
In order to safeguard the dignity of lawyers and prevent individual courts from making it difficult for lawyers, the Supreme Law issued the Rules for the Safety Inspection of the Judicial Police of the People's Courts in 2014, establishing the principle that lawyers do not need to undergo a personal safety examination in court.
Since the rule was issued, lawyers have led by example, and there have been few incidents that endanger the safety of the court because of security loopholes.
In very rare cases such as Quanzhou, as long as communication is carried out in a spirit of mutual respect and understanding, misunderstandings are not difficult to eliminate.
As a self-discipline organization of the bar industry, the Bar Association is responsible for the dual mission of punishing wrongdoing and safeguarding legality.
In the past, individual law associations have been criticized for their emphasis on discipline and loss of protection.
And the decision of the Quanzhou Law Association, both in terms of process and results, is commendable, setting an example for more law associations to perform their duties correctly.
From October 1, which tax benefits will affect our money bags?
SHANGHAI, Oct 1 (Xinhua) -- The new personal income tax law will come into force on January 1, 2019. In order to enable the general public to enjoy the tax reduction dividend as soon as possible, from October 1, the income from wages and salaries actually obtained by taxpayers will be deducted at the starting point of 5,000 yuan per month, and the new tax rate table will be applied.
With the landing of the New Deal, what benefits will affect the people's money bags?
Good 1: The tax cut on income from wages and salaries is obvious
Taxpayers who receive wages and salaries after October 1 can deduct the basic deduction of 5,000 yuan / month and apply the new tax rate table. Most taxpayers have varying degrees of tax cuts, especially for low-and middle-income earners.
According to the tax reduction table of different income groups, the monthly income after deducting the "three risks and one gold" is 8,000 yuan, 10,000 yuan, 20,000 yuan and 50,000 yuan, and the amount of tax payable after the tax reform is 90 yuan, 290 yuan, 1,590 yuan and 9,090 yuan respectively. Compared with the monthly starting point of 3,500 yuan, the corresponding tax reduction ratio is 73.9%, 61.1%, 49.0% and 18.8% respectively.
It is worth noting that, for holiday reasons, the wages paid by units in accordance with the law at the end of September, which should have been paid in October, may be subject to the new basic cost reduction and tax rate table.
To this end, the withholding client software popularized by the tax authorities has provided the corresponding tax calculation function, but the corresponding tax still needs to be declared and paid within the statutory declaration period.
Good 2: The range of low-tax brackets has increased significantly
In addition to raising the threshold, the new tax rate table will be applied from October 1.
The seven-tier tax rate on income from wages and salaries is the same as before and has not changed, but there has been a marked change in the range of tax rates, with a marked increase in the range of low tax rates of 3%, 10% and 20%, a reduction in the range of 25%, while the range of higher tax rates of 30%, 35% and 45% has remained unchanged.
It is worth noting that the tax law has also adjusted the tax rates on income from production and operation, of which the lower limit of the top 35% tax rate has been raised from 100,000 yuan to 500,000 yuan.
This means that individual industrial and commercial households and sole proprietorship partnerships will all benefit from the tax reform.
"Judging from the previous calculation of individual tax cuts for Shanghai taxpayers, the vast majority of taxpayers will fully feel the dividends of individual tax reform, especially for low-and middle-income people." he said.
Lan Min, head of the personal income tax department of the Shanghai Municipal Tax Bureau of the State Administration of Taxation, said.
Good 3: Tax payment services are more convenient and optimized
Since the promulgation of the new personal income tax law, the Shanghai tax authorities have carried out a series of comprehensive and extensive tax publicity activities.
On the one hand, the key tax sources, key enterprises to carry out "one-on-one, point-to-point" policy guidance.
The Pudong New Area Tax Bureau has visited large enterprises such as Apple Trade (Shanghai) Co. Ltd., PayPal (China) Network Technology Co. Ltd. and Red Star Mekaolong Home Group Co. Ltd. These enterprises have a large number of employees, a large workload of withholding and payment, a large amount of tax payment, and the tax authorities have taken the initiative to help and answer questions. The Xuhui District Tax Bureau has visited large labor enterprises in the region, Zhongzhi Financial Consulting Co. Ltd. and Zhongzhi Shanghai Economic and Technical Cooperation Co., to collect the concerns of enterprises in a timely manner, respond to the demands of enterprises and solve the difficulties of enterprises.
On the other hand, to the general public taxpayers, carry out "all-round, multi-dimensional, three-dimensional" tax policy push.
Use the Shanghai tax official website, microblogging public number, microblogging and other channels to push policy hot spots in a timely manner to ensure that policy publicity is in place.
At the same time, since September 28, the Shanghai Tax Micro-Letter Public Number has been on the 12366 Intelligent Consulting Platform to carry out a "targeted" intelligent integrated individual tax reform publicity service through the "artificial + intelligent" tax service consultation.
