Yucheng told the media on Monday that the results of the election showed that the county people did not want Governor Weng's efforts to be in vain. He would inherit Governor Weng's legacy and continue to make efforts to the Japanese and U.S. governments to oppose the relocation of the U.S. military base and the closure of the Putian base.
The U.S. military base in Putian, located in the city of Yicano Bay, Okinawa Prefecture, has been criticized, with the Japanese and U.S. governments agreeing to move it to the Banyoku area of the famous city, but Okinawa people strongly oppose it in the hope of moving the base out of Okinawa.
