The 5th "Disability Voice Month" arrives to pay attention to sex education for young people with disabilities-China New Network
In recent years, the topic of sex education for young people in China has been widely discussed, but the challenge of sex education for young people with disabilities is still very difficult.
Recently, a seminar on the challenges and practical strategies of comprehensive education for people with disabilities was held in Beijing.
How to carry out sex education for children and young people with disabilities has become an important topic of this seminar.
The Report on Sexual Knowledge, Attitudes and Behavior of Children and Young People with Disabilities in China, released at the meeting, showed that the proportion of children with disabilities suffering from sexual harassment and sexual abuse was higher than that of healthy children.
For children and young people with disabilities, more attention is paid to "sexual protection" in the society.
The purpose of the seminar is to explore the promotion of comprehensive sexuality education for children and young people with disabilities in China from three aspects: family support, school education and institutional services, and to provide support to children and young people with disabilities at the source, so that they, like others, have the right to enjoy love at home.
Experts believe that for a long time, the public's understanding of disabled groups in Chinese society has remained at a level that is not deep enough.
Affected by traditional ideas and other factors, China's comprehensive education for people with disabilities, especially children and young people with disabilities, is not in-depth enough.
However, in recent years, with the support of UNESCO and public welfare people, the practice and realization path of sexual and reproductive health education for people with disabilities in China have developed in an all-round way.
According to the Report, children and young people with visual, hearing, intellectual and physical disabilities, although they may have more difficulties in obtaining sexual knowledge and understanding intimate relationships than the general population, have generally developed towards convenience and richness.
Organised by the Shanghai Foundation for the Public Interest and jointly supported by the UNESCO representative office in China, the Beijing representative office of the International Union for the Disabled (France) and the representative office of the United Nations Population Fund in China, the "Seminar on Challenges and Practical Strategies for Comprehensive Sex Education for People with Disabilities" aims to jointly explore the practice and realization path of sexual and reproductive health education for people with disabilities in the context of the Great Strategy for a Healthy China, promote policy makers, educators, researchers, social service organizations, parents' representatives and other stakeholders in the field of special education and integrated education to understand the challenges of comprehensive sexuality education and the right to health of children and young people with disabilities in the future, and to develop a blueprint for the development of comprehensive sexuality education for children and young people with disabilities in China.
BEIJING, Sept 30 (Reuters) -China's central bank on Sunday released net data on scheduled short-term outflows of foreign currency assets, showing that the central bank's short position in foreign currency against local currency forward and futures contracts was zero for 12 consecutive months at the end of August and still had no long positions in the month.
