After 6 years, Tencent welcomes major organizational restructuring to make it clear that there will be no layoffs-China New Network
On the 30th, Tencent announced the official launch of a new round of overall strategic upgrading, the organizational structure after a six-year hiatus ushered in a new round of optimization and adjustment, on the basis of the original seven major business groups (BG) to restructure and integrate into six, and said the adjustment did not involve layoffs.
Tencent new six major business groups.
After six years of re-adjustment of two new business groups appeared.
It is understood that the new business group not only maintains the advantages and characteristics of the deep-ploughed vertical field, but also retains the original enterprise development business group (CDG), interactive entertainment business group (IEG), technical engineering business group (TEG) and micro-messaging business group (WXG). It also highlights the integration effect, and has set up a new cloud and wisdom industry business group (CSIG), platform and content business group (PCG).
The reporter noted that Tencent's original mobile Internet business group (MIG), the former network media business group (OMG) and so on all disappeared, especially OMG, the outside world is very well-known.
Tencent said the newly established platform and content business group (PCG, or Platform & Content Group) will organically split and restructure the former social network business group (SNG), the former mobile Internet business group (MIG) and the former network media business group (OMG), which are highly related and highly integrated with social platforms, traffic platforms, digital content and core technology.
The newly established CSIG, or Cloud and Smart Industries Group, will integrate industry solutions such as Tencent Cloud, Internet +, Wisdom Retail, Education, Health, Security and LBS to promote the digital upgrading of the industry.
'The second half of the Internet is an industrial Internet,' said Ma Huateng, chairman and chief executive of Tencent's board of directors. 'In the first half, Tencent provides high-quality services to users through connectivity. In the second half, we will build on this to help the industry and consumers form a more open new connection ecology.
Response to the "layoff" rumor: Make it clear that there are no layoffs.
After Tencent released the news of the organizational restructuring, it was reported that the adjustment would involve layoffs.
"It is clear that this organizational restructuring will not involve layoffs," Tencent told China New Network. "We will move the business modules as a whole, combine them first and then optimize them."
