Five people have been killed after an illegal migrant boat sank in Turkey's Aegean Sea.
ISTANBUL, Sept 30 (Xinhua) -- At least five people were killed when an inflatable boat carrying illegal migrants capsized in Turkey's Aegean Sea, Turkish media reported on Wednesday.
The inflatable ship, which was due to travel to a Greek island, sank near the Enez area of northwestern Turkey's Edierne province on the same day for an unknown cause, the report said.
At present, it is not clear the number of illegal immigrants on board the sunken inflatable boat.
Search and rescue operations are continuing as it is estimated that there are still people trapped at sea.
The Aegean Sea was once the preferred route for illegal immigrants to be smuggled to the European continent via Turkey.
The number of people smuggled through this channel has been significantly reduced after Turkey controlled it under an agreement with the European Union in March 2016.
But so far this year, the number of smugglers on the channel has rebounded again.
