The relevant departments to improve the rural market, year after year, why is "Li Ge" still repeatedly beaten?
Unlike the urban market, farmers' awareness of rights protection is relatively weak, and many rural areas are remote and in blind areas beyond the reach of regulatory forces, so that fake and inferior commodities have a breeding ground.
A commodity multi-head management, some departments in charge of prices, some in charge of production, some in charge of the market, cross-cutting functions, year-on-year counterfeiting, centralized management of a gust of wind, fake goods escaped the spotlight, and slowly emerged, just after the old holiday, new holidays came out again.
The lack of a long-term regulatory mechanism, the difficulty of purifying the rural market, the low cost of breaking the law and the large benefits have led some illegal traders to use the crooked mind of "going to the mountains and going to the countryside", and some rural areas have become "waste elimination markets".
From food and clothing to well-off, the vast majority of farmers are moving towards development-oriented consumption.
A few days ago, the Central Committee of the Party and the State Council issued the Opinions on Improving the Institutional Mechanism for Promoting Consumption and Further Stimulating the Consumption Potential of Residents, which proposed to promote the upgrading of the consumption of rural residents, with the aim of enabling farmers to "consume", "willing to consume" and "dare to consume", so that rural consumption can truly flourish.
On the one hand, we should deepen reform, eliminate the shortcomings of market supervision and multi-pronged management, improve the network of food safety and product quality supervision according to local conditions, and continuously reduce the space for counterfeiting and selling in rural areas.
On the other hand, we should strengthen law enforcement, open up the supervision of "capillaries", and never allow fake and inferior products to breed and spread in rural areas.
Severe punishment of potholes is the protection of farmers. No matter how hidden the counterfeiters are, they should not be a reason for the breeding of fake and inferior commodities. The relevant departments should clarify their responsibilities, the grass-roots supervision forces should sink, and which link goes wrong, they should be investigated for responsibility, so that the counterfeiters and counterfeiters have no place to hide.
We will strictly close market access, carry out strict qualification examination for producers and operators, check the circulation of the market, let the products come to the right road, clear the road, find ways from the source and root, so that the legal dealers can operate at ease and let the farmers buy at ease.
Activating rural consumption, we should guide the demand for healthy consumption.
With the upgrading of consumption, many farmers not only seek to eat enough and eat well, but also pursue high-quality life such as culture and health, and cannot equate the rural market with "low-quality" and "cheap" paintings.
This requires promoting the extension of e-commerce to the vast rural areas, unblocking the two-way linkage sales channels between urban and rural areas, promoting the integration of the offline industrial development platform and the online electric business trading platform, and supporting the expansion of the new mode of consumption to the rural market; promoting the organic integration of trade and logistics with leisure agriculture, rural tourism and product processing in towns and villages with conditions; and improving the modern rural circulation network system, optimizing the integration of stock facilities and resources, and effectively reducing the cost of rural circulation.
To create a clear and secure market environment for the countryside, so that farmers' consumption is not worried, rural consumption can become more and more prosperous, so as to enhance the sense of acquisition and happiness of farmers' consumption.
From November 1, China will reduce the most-favoured-nation tax rate on some goods, and the total tariff level will be reduced to 7.5%
In accordance with the decision of the 26th executive meeting of the State Council, the Committee on Tariffs and Tariffs of the State Council issued a notice on the 30th to reduce the most-favoured-nation tax rate for some commodities from November 1, 2018.
In accordance with the Notice of the Committee on Tariffs and Tariffs of the State Council on the Reduction of Import Tariffs on Some Commodities, in order to meet the needs of industrial upgrading, reduce the cost of enterprises and meet the multi-level consumption of the masses, the most-favoured-nation tax rate on some industrial goods and other commodities will be reduced from November 1 this year.
There are 1,585 tax items, accounting for about 19% of the total number of tax items in China, and the average tax rate has been reduced from 10.5% to 7.8%, an average decline of 26%.
The tax reduction mainly covers textiles; stone, ceramics and glass products; some steel and base metal products; electromechanical equipment and parts, such as metal processing machinery, textile machinery, engineering machinery, transmission and transmission equipment, electrical equipment, instruments and instruments; and resource-based commodities and primary processed products, such as non-metallic mines, inorganic chemicals, wood and paper products, and precious jade.
At the same time, with the reduction of the overall tariff level, especially the import tariff on medicines and consumer goods for daily use, the tariff rate of the import tax on imported goods will be reduced accordingly.
In order to implement the decision-making and deployment of the Central Committee of the Party and the State Council, China has imposed zero tariffs on the vast majority of imported drugs since May 1 this year, reduced import tariffs on automobiles, parts and components and some consumer goods for daily use since July 1, and implemented the third step of tax reduction on products expanded by the information technology agreement.
The reporter learned from the Committee on Tariffs and Tariffs of the State Council that since this year, after a series of independent adjustments, China's total tariff level will fall from 9.8% in the previous year to 7.5%, an average decline of 23%.
An appropriate reduction in tariffs is conducive to promoting the balanced development of foreign trade, promoting a higher level of opening-up to the outside world, as well as making overall use of both international and domestic resources and promoting domestic supply-side structural reform.
The relevant person in charge of the committee said that this year marks the 40th anniversary of reform and opening-up, and that the initiative to reduce the overall tariff level is a practical action to implement the spirit of General Secretary Xi Jinping's important speech at the Boao Forum for Asia. It is also an important step for China to further expand its opening-up and actively expand its imports in accordance with its own high-quality development needs. This action and initiative shows that China will unswervingly pursue a mutually beneficial and win-win opening-up strategy and, while enhancing its own development momentum, make China's development better benefit the world.
On September 29, Gansu Province Huanxian "Huanxiang People" agricultural products regional public brand conference was held in Nankai District, Tianjin.
Red Army millet, black beans, mountain children pastoral black goats, hardcover bitter buckwheat tea, paper-cutting shadow books, pure hand-made slippers... pieces of beautifully packaged agricultural products are neatly placed on the exhibition stand, and they have a common brand name called "Huanxiang People".
"Building a regional brand of 'Ring Township People' has effectively solved the bottleneck of the development of'many and scattered, small and weak 'agricultural products in Huanxian County, and has become a powerful carrier for poverty alleviation." said the regional public brand conference of "Ring Township People" agricultural products hosted by Huanxian County, Gansu Province, held in Nankai District, Tianjin, on the 29th.
Huanxian is located at the junction of the three provinces and regions of Shaanxi-Gansing. As an "advanced county for grain production in the country", "the land of small grain in China" and "the land of shadow in China", it has a long history and is rich in resources.
Lamb meat, yellow rice wine, buckwheat chopped noodles, swallows noodles soft and other local snacks are often remembered by travellers in other countries.
With the continuous improvement of the level of urbanization in China, the urban population has increased rapidly, and a large number of rural young people have left their hometown to begin urban life.
Yang Qiaojia, an expert in agricultural brand research in China, said: "Now the pace of urban life is fast and the pressure is high, and more and more people are beginning to miss the rural life when they were young. However, 'those who can't go back are called their hometown, and the most beautiful memory is the countryside ', and the brand design of the'people around the countryside' is named after the homesickness and homesickness of the people who are adrift in the county."
Huanxian special climate conditions, long sunshine time, large temperature difference between day and night, special small grain planting conditions.
China is rich in more than 20 small grains, is the land of small grains in China, the yield is the highest in Gansu Province, the quality is among the highest in the country.
Wang Xiaoli, a girl from Huanxian who went to school in Tianjin, attended the briefing as a volunteer. "The people in her hometown are the closest and the taste of her hometown is the most beautiful," she said. "The brand of 'Huanxiang People' has evoked too many of our homesickness, memories and memories of the food there. I hope the brand of 'Huanxiang People' will go further and further and bigger."
Dr. Tan Bin, a researcher at the Institute of Science of the State Food and Material Reserve Bureau, said that through the testing of more than 900 sets of index data, the test data of agricultural products such as buckwheat, bitter buckwheat and black beans in Huanxian County have outstanding advantages, and the content of many physiological active substances in miscellaneous grain is higher than the standard data, and the "Huanxiang people" have the inherent advantage of seizing the high-end grain market in China.
Chai Chun, secretary of the county committee of Huanxian County, said that through the release of the "Huanxiang People" brand, it will further improve the level of quality, standardization and large-scale innovation and development of high-quality agricultural products in Huanxian County, help to shape the good overall image of agricultural products in Huanxian County, and quickly enhance visibility, competitiveness and value added.
Canada's gross domestic product rose 0.2% in July from the previous month, a higher-than-expected increase, raising expectations that the Bank of Canada will raise interest rates next month.
If it does, it would be the central bank's 5th rate hike in a little more than a year.
Analysts interviewed by Reuters had previously forecast a 0.1% increase.
Statistics Canada said on Friday that 12 of the 20 sectors saw growth.
The data is notable because the central bank predicted earlier this month that temporary factors could drag down third-quarter GDP data.
Bank of Canada President Poloz promised Thursday that the central bank would continue to raise interest rates gradually and would keep a close eye on economic data.
The Bank of Canada's next interest rate decision will be on October 24.
The Bank of Canada has raised interest rates four times since July 2017 as the Canadian economy strengthens and unemployment is close to a record low.
Stephen Brown, a senior Canadian economist at CIC Macro, said the country's economy is expected to grow at an annual rate of about 2% in the third quarter.
"This will be higher than the 1.5% expected by the Bank of Canada and will therefore be another reason to expect the Bank of Canada to raise interest rates next month," he said in a note.
Overnight index swaps showed that the market's estimate of the Bank of Canada's chances of raising interest rates in October rose to 78.27% from 76.46%.
South Korea and North Korea's first joint visit to the mouth of the Han River in 65 years
South Korea's Defense Ministry confirmed on Friday that the two Koreas launched a joint visit to the waters at the mouth of the Han and Linjin rivers on the same day.
The initiative is a pre-preparation to ensure the free navigation of civilian vessels on both sides.
A briefing provided to the media by the South Korean Defense Ministry on the same day showed that it was the first time the two sides had conducted a joint visit to the mouth of the Han River since the signing of the Korean War armistice agreement in 1953.
South Korea and North Korea signed a military agreement in September, agreeing to jointly visit waters such as the mouth of the Han River into the sea from November to ensure future environmental protection and tourism development of the waters.
In October, the two Koreas planned a joint survey of the waters at a general-level meeting.
On November 5, a joint survey of Korean-Korean waters was officially launched.
The joint delegation was composed of 20 people, including the Korean and Korean military and experts.
During the visit, neither side carried weapons and banned the use of words and deeds that stimulated each other, according to South Korea's Defense Ministry.
"Because there is no military demarcation line near the mouth of the sea, the area was once an accident-prone area, but through joint visits, it will become a new peaceful area in the future." he said.
The waters jointly visited by the two Koreas are about 70 kilometers long and have a total area of about 280 square kilometers.
South Korea's Defense Ministry said the South Korean side will send six research vessels to detect the depth of the sea to provide basic information for the safe navigation of the waters, and will provide navigation maps for the movement of civilian ships when the investigation is completed.
The two Koreas held summit talks in Pyongyang in October 2007 to reach an agreement on the joint use of the Han and Linjin rivers into the sea, but follow-up talks were stalled by tensions on the peninsula.
Under a military agreement signed by South Korea and North Korea in September, future ships from both sides will need to inform each other in advance before sailing in common waters.
Chinese citizens Guo Yuqin and Mao Runxin lost contact during a trip to Mongolia, the website of the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia said on Thursday.
It is understood that the two were members of the Blue Sky Rescue Team. On October 19, the two contacted friends and relatives in the country and said they were about to explore the mountains near Lake Kusugur and shared their location through a microblog. They have since lost contact and are suspected to have gone to no man's land.
The Chinese Embassy in Mongolia has always attached great importance to the protection of the legitimate rights, interests and security of Chinese citizens in Mongolia, as well as to consular protection and assistance.
After learning of the loss of the above-mentioned two tourists, the Embassy immediately launched an emergency plan for receiving insurance, striving to seize the golden rescue time and make every effort to carry out its work.
The Embassy maintained close communication with the families of the parties concerned, assisted the family in immediately reporting the case to the Mongolian police, and provided the family with a list of translators for choice.
At the first time, the Embassy met with the heads of the Ministry of Foreign Relations, the General Administration of Police and the General Administration of Emergency Situations of Mongolia to inform them of the relevant situation, and asked the Mongolian side to carry out search and rescue as soon as possible, and to maintain close communication with the Mongolian side throughout the search and rescue process to ensure that the latest progress is kept in a timely manner.
At the same time, the Embassy has assisted the families in issuing search notices in Mongolia, and has widely mobilized overseas Chinese and Chinese enterprises in Mongolia to take an active part in the search for people, provide effective clues, and provide relevant assistance to a number of blue sky rescue workers who have gone to Mongolia to assist in the rescue.
Under the strong impetus of the embassy, the Mongolian side sent a rescue team at the first time and promised to waive search and rescue fees.
The General Directorate of the Mongolian Police and the General Directorate of Emergency Situations instructed the police and emergency departments of Kusugur Province to make every effort to search and rescue.
As Lake Kusugur is located on the border between northern Mongolia and Russia, is remote, sparsely populated, transportation and communications are extremely difficult, and Mongolia has now entered a severe winter, with temperatures as low as about minus 20 degrees, the local police and emergency departments have overcome great difficulties, mobilized almost all the police force and mobilized local herdsmen to carry out a wide range of carpet search and rescue operations around the two men's lost location for days through horse riding, walking and visiting herdsmen.
At the same time, in view of the special situation in the pastoral areas, the Mongolian side has been issuing search notices through the broadcast cycle for many days.
The relevant staff of the domestic Blue Sky Rescue Team have also come to Mongolia to actively participate in the rescue with the Mongolian side.
The safety of the two lost personnel has always touched our hearts.
It has been more than 10 days since the two men were lost, and the Embassy has received some clues, but the two have not yet been found, and search and rescue operations are still under intense strain.
The Embassy will always pay continuous attention to the matter on the basis of the principle of "people-oriented", push the Mongolian side to continue its full search and rescue efforts and provide maximum assistance to the families of the parties concerned.
The Embassy calls on compatriots and enterprises in Mongolia to contact the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia at the first time if they are informed of relevant clues.
